<h2>f-min parameter.

<h4>
something like:
<h3>f-min is defined as the lowest frequency of all the received echoes.
It is partly a measure of the quality of the actual ionosonde.<h3>
The f-min for the ionograms at IRF is normally 1 - 2 MHz. 
<h4>
christer@irf.se
</DOC>
