<hr><h1>Why do scaling at all?</h1>
<hr> 
<H3>This will be a collection of reasons for and against scaling of Ionograms</h3>
<hr> <h5>(under development)</h5>
<h2>Full scaling according to the green book from 1957!</h2>
<h2>The French -- local name for scaling to three parameters.</h2>

<hr>
<h3>the parameters: (under development)</h3>
 <a href="http://u2.irf.se/~ionogram/pfmin.html">f-min </a>
 <a href="http://u2.irf.se/~ionogram/phtml.html"> h'Es</a>
 <a href="http://u2.irf.se/~ionogram/pfoEs.html"> fo-Es </a>
 <a href="http://u2.irf.se/~ionogram/pTypeEs.html">TypeEs </a>
 <a href="http://u2.irf.se/~ionogram/pfbEs.html"> fbEs </a>
 <a href="http://u2.irf.se/~ionogram/phpE.html">h'E </a>
 <a href="http://u2.irf.se/~ionogram/pfoE.html">foE </a>
 <a href="http://u2.irf.se/~ionogram/phpf.html"> h'f </a>
 <a href="http://u2.irf.se/~ionogram/pfoF1.html">foF1</a>
