<BODY BACKGROUND="/pictures/lhwmwall.gif" LINK="#0000ff" VLINK="#ff0000" TEXT="#000000">
<A HREF=/home.html><IMG SRC="/pictures/smallfront.gif" WIDTH="100" HEIGHT="40"> </A>
<h2> What's new on this WWW server </h2>
<h3> <a href="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/sigpac"> SIGPAC </a> </h3>
Forest monitoring by satellite and integrated watershed management in Costa Rica. (Spanish and English version available)<HR>
<h3><a href="http://hobbes.rug.ac.be/~kristoff">Faculty of Agricultural Sciences and Applied Biological Sciences</a> </h3>
The home page of the faculty is coming up! Of course still under construction. This page is made by Kristoff Thierens and resides at the www-server of <a href="http://hobbes.rug.ac.be/">BIOMATH.</a> <HR>
<h3> <a href="/members/bart/paper/paper.html"> The Zwalm catchment: A meta database </h3> </a>
The Laboratory of Hydrology and Water Management has a test site in the South East of East Flanders. It is equiped with a hydrological monitoring network. This report introduces the site, gives an overview of the available data and describes the implementation of the test site in a GIS package (Grass). <HR>
<h3> <a href="/projects/VLIR/vlir.html"> VLIR project </a></h3>
LHWM is starting up a collaborative project with the Institute for Aride Zones in Kebili Tunisia.
The project handles quantity and quality problems of geothermal water used in the horticulture in Southern Tunisia.
A description of the project is included. Currently only a French vesrion is available.
<HR>
<h3> <a href="/brows/remotess.html">Remote Sensing links</a>  </h3>
A list of links about remote sensing. Information on different platforms, Space Agencies and related sites.
<HR>
<h3> <a href="/projects/VLIR/picttunis.html"> Pictures from the south </a> </h3> 
Pictures from the south of Tunisia. These pictures give you some idea of how it looks like between Gabes and Tozeur. Tunisia is getting more and more on internet. You can find links to <a href="/brows/tunis.html"> servers and pages in and about Tunisia </a> with info about the country, the people and the culture. <HR>
<h3> <a href="/brows/irri.html"> Irrigation links </a> </h3>
The laboratory of Hydrlogy and Water Management is starting a project on irrigation in <a href="/projects/VLIR/vlir.html"> Southern Tunisia </a>. Here you can find some links related to this subject.
<HR>

</B>
