<BR> <P>
<A NAME="subcat">&#160;</A><H3><A NAME="SECTION00041200000000000000">The Passemare and Sassegem Subcatchments </A></H3>
<P>
The Passemare catchment (Figure&nbsp;<A HREF="node10.html#zwalmps">1</A>) is situated in the north of
the Zwalm catchment near Velzeke (Map 30/1-2; 1:25000).  
Passemare beek is a second order (Horton order) stream with
a drainage area of 2.52&nbsp;km <IMG WIDTH=6 HEIGHT=9 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2775" SRC="img5.gif"  > . The total channel length is 2.97&nbsp;km. 
The average slope is
around 5&nbsp;% (channel slope 4.8&nbsp;% and hill slope 5.6&nbsp;%). 
The land use is mainly agriculture with an urban area in the east 
of the subcatchment.
<P>
The Sassegem catchment (Figure&nbsp;<A HREF="node10.html#zwalmps">1</A>) is situated in the extreme 
south of the catchment. Slopes, average of 8.5&nbsp;%, are steeper than in 
the northern subcatchment. With a drainage area of
2.49&nbsp;km <IMG WIDTH=6 HEIGHT=9 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2775" SRC="img5.gif"  >  and a total channel length of 2.92&nbsp;km, 
the catchment has an average drainage
density comparable to the Passemare catchment. The Sassegem catchment is mainly
covered by forests (50&nbsp;%) and agricultural land. 
Sassegembeek is also a second order stream.
<P>
<BR> <HR>
