 <A NAME="tex2html319" HREF="node14.html"><IMG WIDTH=37 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="next" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html317" HREF="node12.html"><IMG WIDTH=26 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="up" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html311" HREF="node12.html"><IMG WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="previous" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/previous_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html321" HREF="node1.html"><IMG WIDTH=65 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="contents" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/contents_motif.gif"></A>  <BR>
<B> Next:</B> <A NAME="tex2html320" HREF="node14.html">Topographic Maps</A>
<B>Up:</B> <A NAME="tex2html318" HREF="node12.html">Permanent Data of the </A>
<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME="tex2html312" HREF="node12.html">Permanent Data of the </A>
<BR> <P>
<H3><A NAME="SECTION00042100000000000000">Digital Elevation Map</A></H3>
<P>
The DEM for the Zwalm catchment (Figure&nbsp;<A HREF="node12.html#demps">2</A>)
has been delivered by the National Institute of Geography
of Belgium. The original non-projected raster model has a 
resolution of 1' in the <I>x</I> and <I>y</I> directions.
The <I>z</I> values in are stored in integer format so the highest error on the 
elevations is 0.5. The DEM is processed from the original format 
to a TIN and grid model in order to be readable by the GIS software.
Two new grid models are made based on this process:
<UL><LI> A model with a grid space of 50&nbsp;m in both <I>x</I> and <I>y</I> directions: 
      291 rows and 351 columns;<LI> A model with a grid space of 30&nbsp;m in both <I>x</I> and <I>y</I> directions: 
      485 rows and 585 columns.
      This DEM is processed in GRASS, in UTM coordinates and in 
      Lambert coordinates. 
      The outer coordinates can be seen in the corresponding header files.
</UL>
These DEM data are processed using a software package from the
U.S. Geological Survey (USGS) in order to calculate
slopes and topological indices for each pixel and for modeling the 
watershed and the network of channels. This software is able to mask pits. 
For flat areas the 
flow direction can be wrong because of a small digitalization 
error or because of
the resolution in <I>z</I>. This error depends on the 
resolution of the grid and the
scale of the model&nbsp;[<A HREF="node63.html#gyasi93"><EM>GyasiAgyei, </EM><EM>GyasiAgyei</EM><EM>
  1993</EM></A>]. The
modification of this DEM is still in progress in order to make a good mask file
for the watershed. This is done by creating a dike in 
the <I>z</I> values at the border
of the catchment. This modified DEM should not be used to calculate the
other data as it is manipulated in order to get a better fitting to the
watershed digitized from a non-digital map. 
The processing of DEMs still needs to be researched in more detail. 
From the DEM (resolution 30&nbsp;m) the following derived 
data are available in GRASS. These data can be compared 
with the available divide
and network of channels as they were digitized from the topographic maps.
<UL><A NAME="grassfiles">&#160;</A><LI> The divide of the catchment, as vector and raster files;<LI> The network of channels, as vector and raster files;<LI> The topological indices for each pixel of the catchment;<LI> The slopes for each pixel of the catchment.
</UL>
Subregions of these DEMs can easily be created and even higher and lower 
resolution are possible. One has to consider, however, that further processing
will invoke a bigger error when processed by algorithms 
such as linear interpolation and kriging.
<P>
<HR><A NAME="tex2html319" HREF="node14.html"><IMG WIDTH=37 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="next" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html317" HREF="node12.html"><IMG WIDTH=26 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="up" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html311" HREF="node12.html"><IMG WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="previous" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/previous_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html321" HREF="node1.html"><IMG WIDTH=65 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="contents" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/contents_motif.gif"></A>  <BR>
