<BR> <P>
<H3><A NAME="SECTION00042400000000000000">Soil Maps and Soil Properties</A></H3>
<P>
LWHM owns 2 RGB soil maps on a scale of 1:10000 in raster format and 2 black and
white soil maps on a scale of 1:20000. 
These files in raster format will be used to 
allow faster digitalization of the soil maps. The raster file will be 
transferred to a vectormap by thinning the lines and converting them to closed 
polygons. Categorization, i.e., assigning attribute values to  
corresponding fields
in the database, will be done manually and can take some time. Until these
data become available we refer to the literature for soil propoerty
data. Kotb&nbsp;kotb93 conducted
a study of hydraulic properties for the Zwalm catchment. 
The objective of the study was to investigate 
the spatial variability of the hydraulic properties on a field scale, 
with an attempt also to extend this to higher scales. In this work one can find
a more detailed overview of the different soil properties for the catchment 
zones that were tested.
A more general description can be found in Troch&nbsp;patroch93.
<P>
<BR> <HR>
