 <A NAME="tex2html393" HREF="node21.html"><IMG WIDTH=37 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="next" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html391" HREF="node17.html"><IMG WIDTH=26 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="up" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html387" HREF="node19.html"><IMG WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="previous" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/previous_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html395" HREF="node1.html"><IMG WIDTH=65 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="contents" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/contents_motif.gif"></A>  <BR>
<B> Next:</B> <A NAME="tex2html394" HREF="node21.html">Data Collection During Remote </A>
<B>Up:</B> <A NAME="tex2html392" HREF="node17.html">Time Dependent Data: Continuous </A>
<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME="tex2html388" HREF="node19.html">Quantitative Hydrologic Data </A>
<BR> <P>
<A NAME="qual">&#160;</A><H3><A NAME="SECTION00043300000000000000">Qualitative Hydrologic Data </A></H3>
<P>
Apart from the quantitative hydrologic data collected at the Zwalm catchment,
water quality is also monitored, at the outlet of the
Zwalm (station 101 Neder). The station consists of a sampler
and a sensor. The sampler collects, by means of a pump, hourly samples of
10&nbsp;cc. The samples for each day are stored in the same sampling bottle. The
sampler is emptied every 10 days by staff of the Laboratory of Agrochemistry,
and the samples are analyzed in the lab. All chemical properties can be
analyzed but only a few are monitored regularly (nitrates, phosphates, and
potassium). Other properties are analyzed for specific studies only.
The sensor is installed near the sampler. This sensor logs
properties such as water temperature, redox-potential, and dissolved oxygen.
<P>
<BR> <HR>
<P><ADDRESS>
<I>Bart Cosyn <BR>
Thu Jul 25 13:19:15 MDT 1996</I>
