<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Soil Moisture</TITLE>
<META NAME="description" CONTENT="Soil Moisture">
<META NAME="keywords" CONTENT="paper">
<META NAME="resource-type" CONTENT="document">
<META NAME="distribution" CONTENT="global">
<LINK REL=STYLESHEET HREF="paper.css">
</HEAD>
<BODY LANG="EN">
 <A NAME="tex2html465" HREF="node26.html"><IMG WIDTH=37 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="next" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html463" HREF="node24.html"><IMG WIDTH=26 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="up" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html457" HREF="node24.html"><IMG WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="previous" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/previous_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html467" HREF="node1.html"><IMG WIDTH=65 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="contents" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/contents_motif.gif"></A>  <BR>
<B> Next:</B> <A NAME="tex2html466" HREF="node26.html">Surface Roughness</A>
<B>Up:</B> <A NAME="tex2html464" HREF="node24.html">Ground Truth Data Collection</A>
<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME="tex2html458" HREF="node24.html">Ground Truth Data Collection</A>
<BR> <P>
<H3><A NAME="SECTION00053100000000000000">Soil Moisture</A></H3>
<P>
Given the different spatial resolution of the SAR images collected from 
the above mentioned platforms (aircraft, shuttle, and satellites), 
different sampling strategies were chosen
for each specific campaign. During the EMAC aircraft flights,
soil moisture was determined along transects oriented parallel 
and perpendicular to the flight lines ( <IMG WIDTH=26 HEIGHT=14 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2843" SRC="img13.gif"  > - <IMG WIDTH=36 HEIGHT=14 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2845" SRC="img14.gif"  >  from
magnetic north). These transects were located in agricultural fields in both 
the Passemarebeek and Sassegembeek. Sampling took place along these 
transects every 25&nbsp;m. A distance of 5&nbsp;m was selected when high variations 
in soil moisture were expected.
<P>
Two methods were used to estimate volumetric soil moisture content. 
The first method is the gravimetric method. At each point, soil samples 
were taken by means of an auger at 0-5&nbsp;cm,
5-10&nbsp;cm and 10-20&nbsp;cm. This procedure is repeated 3 times 
at each location. In April,
when very wet conditions prevailed, only soil samples at 0-5&nbsp;cm 
and 5-10&nbsp;cm were collected.
From these samples a mixed sample at each depth is prepared and 
dried in the oven at  <IMG WIDTH=36 HEIGHT=14 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2847" SRC="img15.gif"  > C for 24 hours. The gravimetric 
moisture content <I>w</I> is then given by
<P> <IMG WIDTH=500 HEIGHT=44 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="equation1686" SRC="img16.gif"  > <P>
where  <IMG WIDTH=28 HEIGHT=28 ALIGN=MIDDLE ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2851" SRC="img17.gif"  >  is the weight of the wet sample and  <IMG WIDTH=25 HEIGHT=28 ALIGN=MIDDLE ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2853" SRC="img18.gif"  >  is the weight 
of the dry sample. During each experiment undisturbed soil 
core samples were collected to determine average bulk density along 
the transects. Knowing the bulk density  <IMG WIDTH=16 HEIGHT=18 ALIGN=MIDDLE ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2855" SRC="img19.gif"  > , 
the volumetric moisture content  <IMG WIDTH=8 HEIGHT=14 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2857" SRC="img20.gif"  >  is calculated as
<P> <IMG WIDTH=500 HEIGHT=40 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="equation1690" SRC="img21.gif"  > <P>
where  <IMG WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=18 ALIGN=MIDDLE ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2859" SRC="img22.gif"  >  is the density of water.
The same sampling strategy was chosen during the SIR-C overpasses. 
During satellite
observations another strategy was chosen. For ERS-1 and 
J-ERS-1 observations all
agricultural fields where sampling was possible (bare soil, 
pasture, and short vegetation
fields) were sampled. On average, for each field 3-6 auger samples 
were colleced at depths 0-5&nbsp;cm and 5-10&nbsp;cm. 
It was decided, given the shallow penetration depth of the
ERS-1 SAR instrument (C-band) that the 10-20&nbsp;cm sampling 
was redundant. However, for
J-ERS-1 and in dry conditions a 10-20&nbsp;cm sampling 
depth is believed to be relevant for moisture profile inversion.
<P>
A second method used to estimate volumetric soil moisture content 
is time domain reflectometry (TDR). 
At certain locations a hole ( <IMG WIDTH=106 HEIGHT=25 ALIGN=MIDDLE ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2861" SRC="img23.gif"  > &nbsp;cm) was dug, 
taking care to preserve the soil undisturbed along three walls of the hole. 
Along these three sides the TDR probe was introduced at a depth of 2.5&nbsp;cm 
and 7.5&nbsp;cm. This yields three estimates of volumetric moisture content 
at depth 0-5&nbsp;cm and 5-10&nbsp;cm. 
In addition, three vertical measurements were taken 
yielding estimates of volumetric
moisture content integrated over the depth of the probe. The TRIME TDR
instrument uses the following empirical relationship to convert
measured dielectric constant  <IMG WIDTH=6 HEIGHT=9 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2863" SRC="img24.gif"  >  into a volumetric moisture content
 <IMG WIDTH=8 HEIGHT=14 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2857" SRC="img20.gif"  > &nbsp;[<A HREF="node63.html#Top80"><EM>Topp  et al., </EM><EM>Topp  et al.</EM><EM>
  1980</EM></A>]:
<P> <IMG WIDTH=510 HEIGHT=22 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="equation1695" SRC="img25.gif"  > <P>
The Tektronix cable tester stores the TDR wave forms on the hard disk of a 
portable computer.
The analysis of the TDR wave forms is then done in the laboratory. 
The conversion to volumetric moisture content is done 
following Heimovara and De Water&nbsp;heim93.
<P>
<HR><A NAME="tex2html465" HREF="node26.html"><IMG WIDTH=37 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="next" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html463" HREF="node24.html"><IMG WIDTH=26 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="up" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html457" HREF="node24.html"><IMG WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="previous" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/previous_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html467" HREF="node1.html"><IMG WIDTH=65 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="contents" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/contents_motif.gif"></A>  <BR>
