<H3><A NAME="SECTION00053500000000000000">Corner Reflectors</A></H3>
<P>
For the EMAC campaigns in April and August 
corner relectors were positioned
to calibrate the images (Table&nbsp;<A HREF="node28.html#reflectors">3</A>).
These corner reflectors
are not seen by the ERS-1 satellite and their visibility in SIR-C images is
unpredictable as they are positioned in order to have the best reflection for
the EMAC campaign.
The characteristics of the corner reflectors for the April campaign are:
<DL ><DT><STRONG>small corner reflector</STRONG>
<DD> 
  <UL><LI> dimensions: side = 0.7&nbsp;m; hypothenuse =  <IMG WIDTH=83 HEIGHT=27 ALIGN=MIDDLE ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2921" SRC="img47.gif"  > &nbsp;m;<LI> maximum backscattering of crossection at 1.3&nbsp;Ghz 12.8&nbsp;dB and
           5.3&nbsp;Ghz 25.0&nbsp;dB;<LI> they are expected to be visible in EMAC images in the C and X bands
           and perhaps in the L band.
  </UL>
<DT><STRONG>big corner reflector</STRONG>
<DD> 
  <UL><LI> dimensions: side = 0.7&nbsp;m; hypothenuse =  <IMG WIDTH=92 HEIGHT=27 ALIGN=MIDDLE ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2923" SRC="img48.gif"  > &nbsp;m;<LI> maximum backscattering of crossection at 1.3&nbsp;Ghz 22.8&nbsp;dB and
           5.3&nbsp;Ghz 31.0&nbsp;dB;<LI> they are expected to be visible in EMAC images 
           in the C, X, and L bands and perhaps in SIR-C images.
  </UL> 
 </DL>
<P><A NAME="1740">&#160;</A><A NAME="images">&#160;</A> <IMG WIDTH=612 HEIGHT=598 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="table1739" SRC="img49.gif"  > <BR>
<STRONG>Table 4:</STRONG> Available SAR Images for the Zwalm Catchment (As of 8.11.1994)<BR>
