<BR> <P>
<H2><A NAME="SECTION00062000000000000000">How to Introduce Yourself to GRASS</A></H2>
<P>
GRASS contains a large amount of tutorial data and there are many
helpful sites (mailing lists, World Wide Web sites, etc.) to
introduce people to GRASS. On the GRASS
server at CRS4 (workstation ``saturn.crs4.it'') most of the documents are 
downloaded and reside in the GRASS home directory in ``info''.
<DL ><DT><STRONG>GRASS users list</STRONG>
<DD>
    A mailing list to which
    GRASS users can post any questions on compiling, using,
    and adapting GRASS to their needs. The address of the mailing list 
    is <code>grassu-list@moon.cecer.army.mil</code>;
<DT><STRONG>GRASS newsgroup</STRONG>
<DD>
    For those who have access to a news server, the
    contents of the GRASS users list are available in
    <A NAME="tex2html9" HREF="news:info.grass.user">info.grass.user</A> and
    <A NAME="tex2html10" HREF="news:listserv.grass.user">listserv.grass.user</A>;
<DT><STRONG>World Wide Web (WWW)</STRONG>
<DD>
    GRASS has a 
    <A NAME="tex2html11" HREF="http://www.cecer.army.mil/grass/GRASS.main.html">home page</A>
    on WWW. The 
    <A NAME="tex2html12" HREF="http://www.crs4.it/~ sek/remotesmmhome.html">EC project home page</A>
    [<A HREF="node63.html#pancoskledec94"><EM>Paniconi  et al., </EM><EM>Paniconi  et al.</EM><EM>
  1994</EM></A>]
    also contains links to these GRASS sites and other related GIS pages.
<DT><STRONG>Archive</STRONG>
<DD>
    GRASS users and programmers have set up two WWW sites with an 
    <A NAME="tex2html13" HREF="http://soils.ecn.purdue.edu/~ mccauley/grassu/">archive</A>
    and an 
    <A NAME="tex2html14" HREF="http://soils.ecn.purdue.edu/~ aggrass/">online reference manual.</A>
<P>
 </DL>
<P>
For true novices to GRASS or for handling new modules in GRASS it is
advisable to start by using X-GRASS. 
As X-GRASS is not yet completely alpha tested it is likewise not advisable
to use X-GRASS for more advanced work.
<P>
<BR> <HR>
<P><ADDRESS>
<I>Bart Cosyn <BR>
Thu Jul 25 13:19:15 MDT 1996</I>
