<HEAD>
<TITLE>Transformation of Vector Data in GRASS</TITLE>
<META NAME="description" CONTENT="Transformation of Vector Data in GRASS">
<META NAME="keywords" CONTENT="paper">
<META NAME="resource-type" CONTENT="document">
<META NAME="distribution" CONTENT="global">
<LINK REL=STYLESHEET HREF="paper.css">
</HEAD>
<BODY LANG="EN">
 <A NAME="tex2html761" HREF="node52.html"><IMG WIDTH=37 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="next" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html759" HREF="node48.html"><IMG WIDTH=26 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="up" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html755" HREF="node50.html"><IMG WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="previous" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/previous_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html763" HREF="node1.html"><IMG WIDTH=65 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="contents" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/contents_motif.gif"></A>  <BR>
<B> Next:</B> <A NAME="tex2html762" HREF="node52.html">GRASS Setup for the </A>
<B>Up:</B> <A NAME="tex2html760" HREF="node48.html">GRASS and the Different </A>
<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME="tex2html756" HREF="node50.html">Transformation of Raster Data </A>
<BR> <P>
<H3><A NAME="SECTION00074300000000000000">Transformation of Vector Data in GRASS</A></H3>
<P>
Transformation of vector data in GRASS is problematic, but has been
resolved by writing some input and output modules in C.
The actual transformation is not discussed in this section, but only
an overview of the format of a GRASS vector file in ascii is
given. Ascii is not the format normally used by GRASS for vector data,
but it is a format that can be easily imported and exported 
from GRASS using ``v.in.ascii'' and ``v.out.ascii''.
Moreover vector files in the usual format, binary, can be easily 
converted to and from ascii.
<P>
A vector ascii file includes a 14-line header and a 2-column data list. 
In GRASS one can digitize in 3 modes:
<DL ><DT><STRONG>Site mode (point data)</STRONG>
<DD> 
  These data are not stored as vector but as 
  sites files. The format of these files is very clear and they can be 
  manipulated as point data (cfr.&nbsp;<A HREF="node49.html#points">5.4.1</A>).
<P>
  <DT><STRONG>Line mode (line data)</STRONG>
<DD>
  These data are stored as vector data. The label for
  marking these data is ``L''. This label and the number of points 
  creating the line are mentioned before each data list. 
  The category value of a line is mentioned
  on the bottom of each data list.
  An example is the following:
  <PRE>         ORGANIZATION: US Army Const. Eng. Rsch. La 
         DIGIT DATE:   Mon Nov 14 11:58:03 
         DIGIT NAME:   grass 
         MAP NAME:     zwalm.dxf 
         MAP DATE: 
         MAP SCALE:    2400 
         OTHER INFO: 
         ZONE:         0 
         WEST EDGE:    99407.830695 
         EAST EDGE:    112665.390625 
         SOUTH EDGE:   161609.895833 
         NORTH EDGE:   177347.916667 
         MAP THRESH:   0 
         VERTI: 
         L  2 
         161769.69299 102697.02642 
         161810.631155 102911.7711</PRE>
<P>
  <DT><STRONG>Area mode (polygon data)</STRONG>
<DD>
  The label for marking these data is ``A''.
  The format of an area or polygon vector differs from a line vector in two
  ways. First, area vectors have the advantage of
  being closed. Using ``v.area'' enables one to highlight or color a 
  selected area and to obtain information about the area such as perimeter 
  distance or surface area. Second,
  as a polygon has to be closed, the last point of each area is the same
  as the first point. Thus, for instance, an triangle consists of 4 points.
  An example is the following:
  <PRE>         ORGANIZATION: US Army Const. Eng. Rsch. La 
         DIGIT DATE:   Mon Nov 14 11:58:03 
         DIGIT NAME:   grass 
         MAP NAME:     zwalm.dxf 
         MAP DATE: 
         MAP SCALE:    2400 
         OTHER INFO: 
         ZONE:         0 
         WEST EDGE:    99407.830695 
         EAST EDGE:    112665.390625 
         SOUTH EDGE:   161609.895833 
         NORTH EDGE:   177347.916667 
         MAP THRESH:   0 
         VERTI: 
         A  4 
         161769.69299 102697.02642 
         161810.631155 102911.7711 
         161000.631155 102000.7711 
         161769.69299 102697.02642</PRE>
<P>
 </DL><HR><A NAME="tex2html761" HREF="node52.html"><IMG WIDTH=37 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="next" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html759" HREF="node48.html"><IMG WIDTH=26 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="up" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html755" HREF="node50.html"><IMG WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="previous" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/previous_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html763" HREF="node1.html"><IMG WIDTH=65 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="contents" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/contents_motif.gif"></A>  <BR>
