<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME="tex2html799" HREF="node53.html">Definition of the ``Location'' </A>
<BR> <P>
<H3><A NAME="SECTION00081100000000000000">UTM Coordinates</A></H3>
<P>
The out layer UTM coordinates of the catchment are:
north:      5639529 m <BR> 
south:      5623956 m <BR> 
east:       559067  m <BR> 
west:       547210  m
<P>
The middle point of the Zwalm catchment is, in UTM coordinates:
5632285.313 N <BR> 
552864.433 E
<P>
The maximum swath width of images will be around 100 km (ERS-1).
J-ERS-1 has a swath width of 75 km. ERS-1 is in a geodetic phase of 180
days so the positioning of the images is very unpredictable. For that 
reason an area of about 200&nbsp;km <IMG WIDTH=6 HEIGHT=9 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2775" SRC="img5.gif"  >  is chosen as the default area for the 
Zwalm catchment. A resolution smaller than the minimal resolution of the
images is chosen. In the GRASS documentation it is mentioned that redefining 
the default settings is not possible, but by
editing the file ``DEFAULT_WIND'' in the ``PERMANENT'' mapset
it is possible to manipulate the default
settings. Manipulating the
resolution is not necessary as it is possible to increase or decrease 
the resolution of the imported images, independent of the default settings.
For the outer coordinates you must be sure that the imported image fits
within the default parameters.
<P>
The region definition in UTM coordinates is:
north:      5735000 <BR> 
south:      5535000 <BR> 
east:       652800 <BR> 
west:       452800 <BR> 
cols:       20000 <BR> 
rows:       20000 <BR> 
e-w resol:  10 <BR> 
n-s resol:  10
<P>
This area is part of the UTM zone&nbsp;31. The reference ellipsoid 
is the Hayford ellipsoid. The Hayford ellipsoid has a half big axis of
6378388&nbsp;m and excentricity of 0.0818541.
<P>
<BR> <HR>
<P><ADDRESS>
<I>Bart Cosyn <BR>
Thu Jul 25 13:19:15 MDT 1996</I>
