<BODY LANG="EN">
 <A NAME="tex2html817" HREF="node56.html"><IMG WIDTH=37 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="next" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html815" HREF="node53.html"><IMG WIDTH=26 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="up" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html809" HREF="node54.html"><IMG WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="previous" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/previous_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html819" HREF="node1.html"><IMG WIDTH=65 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="contents" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/contents_motif.gif"></A>  <BR>
<B> Next:</B> <A NAME="tex2html818" HREF="node56.html">Lambert Coordinates</A>
<B>Up:</B> <A NAME="tex2html816" HREF="node53.html">Definition of the ``Location'' </A>
<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME="tex2html810" HREF="node54.html">UTM Coordinates</A>
<BR> <P>
<H3><A NAME="SECTION00081200000000000000">Row and Column Setup</A></H3>
<P>
For unreferenced images a project 
ZWALMrc is set up. The same rules as for the UTM project are used.
The characteristics are:
north:      50000 <BR> 
south:      -50000 <BR> 
east:       50000 <BR> 
west:       -50000 <BR> 
cols:       100000 <BR> 
rows:       100000 <BR> 
e-w resol:  1 <BR> 
n-s resol:  1
<P>
<P><A NAME="2050">&#160;</A><A NAME="regionps">&#160;</A><A NAME="tex2htmlfigure2048" HREF="img58.gif"><IMG WIDTH=132 HEIGHT=111 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="figure2047" SRC="Timg58.gif"></A><BR>
<STRONG>Figure 4:</STRONG> Region definition for a row colmun setup in GRASS.<BR>
<P>
<P>
In a ``row column'' (rc) setup it is advisable to put a negative 
value for the north-south
identifiers&nbsp;[<A HREF="node63.html#grassref93"><EM>CERL, </EM><EM>CERL</EM><EM>1993</EM>b</A>]. Using the tool ``d.what.rast''
will then show, except for the negative values in the <I>y</I> direction,
the position in rows and columns referenced to the upper left corner. 
An example is shown in Figure&nbsp;<A HREF="node55.html#regionps">4</A>.
In this way any ERS-1 or J-ERS-1 images should fit within the default region.
<P>
This GRASS rc project is set up in order to receive unreferenced images. 
It should also
allow the user to see the images and data (mainly raster) in row and
columns. This could be useful for relative positioning and for applications
that require an indication of the row-column positioning, for example
the USGS software and associated tools require input in
rows and columns. This setup is also needed to allow georeferencing to
the UTM projection. Therefore all data needed for georefencing can be put 
in this project. The routines ``i.vpoint'' and ``i.rectify'' 
are two of the few GRASS
applications that allow switching between locations. In fact before
runnning ``i.vpoints'' (vector data) or ``i.points'' (raster data), the user has
to run ``i.group'' to collect different bands of the same image into
one group. Also, ``i.target'' must be run to tell GRASS in which
location to put the resulting georeferenced images.
<P>
<BR> <HR>
<P><ADDRESS>
<I>Bart Cosyn <BR>
Thu Jul 25 13:19:15 MDT 1996</I>
