<BR> <P>
<H2><A NAME="SECTION000111000000000000000">Downloading the Software</A></H2>
<P>
The latest release of GRASS is GRASS4.1 and dates from May 1993.
Intermediate releases of particular programs of the software
are frequently announced and made available on the GRASS server. 
In the world of GRASS the word ``moon'' stands for the 
<A NAME="tex2html19" HREF="ftp://moon.cecer.army.mil">ftp server</A>
of the GRASS project, which 
can be accessed by anonymous ftp.
<P>
On moon you can find, apart from the source code, compiled
versions of the software for particular platforms,
the tutorial ``Global''
and ``Spearfish'' datasets,
user and programmer list archives, and contributed software from
GRASS programmers not affiliated with 
USA-CERL. Upon connecting to moon, go to the subdirectory ``grass''. 
You will see an overview of subdirectories,
the most important one being subdirectory ``grass4.1''. 
There you will find all the source code in
``release'', and also the update packages (``update_packages'') and 
manuals (``documents''). An easier way to access the ftp 
server is by using the Mosaic or Netscape browsers for the
World Wide Web. USA-CERL has a 
<A NAME="tex2html20" HREF="http://www.cecer.army.mil/GRASS.main.html">WWW server</A>,
and also direct access to
<A NAME="tex2html21" HREF="ftp://moon.cecer.army.mil">moon.</A>
<P>
The original source codes can be found in ``grass/grass4.1/release''.
This directory contains 5 subdirectories in which the complete release of
GRASS4.1 (tutorials and documents included) can be found. As it is
impossible to retrieve recursive subdirectories, you have to enter each
subdirectory individually and retrieve all the files. The files are
compressed by the UNIX command ``compress'' and archived by ``cpio''.
How can you put all the files together in one cpio file?
<UL><LI> Concatenate all the files with the same name
        (``cat name.cpio.Z.* &gt; name.cpio.Z'');<LI> Uncompress (``uncompress name.cpio.Z'');<LI> Unarchive (``cpio -icdu &lt; name.cpio'').
</UL>
In this way all appropriate subdirectories will be created.
<P>
<BR> <HR>
<P><ADDRESS>
<I>Bart Cosyn <BR>
Thu Jul 25 13:19:15 MDT 1996</I>
