<BR> <P>
<H2><A NAME="SECTION000112000000000000000">Compiling GRASS4.1</A></H2>
<P>
The installation manual&nbsp;[<A HREF="node63.html#grassinst93"><EM>CERL, </EM><EM>CERL</EM><EM>1993</EM>a</A>] 
is available at CRS4 in directory
<PRE>/usr/people/grass/docs/grass/installGuide.ps</PRE>
This manual provides complete instructions for compiling 
GRASS on different platforms. Some knowledge of UNIX, C,
makefiles, libraries, and shell scripts is required, but here are 
some of the basics for the compilation procedure:
<DL ><DT><STRONG>Preliminaries</STRONG>
<DD>
  Before compiling, some shell environment variables
  need to be defined. For c-shell use
  ``setenv GIS /usr/people/grass/Grass4.1'' and
  ``setenv GISDBASE /usr/people/grass/data''.
  For Korn shell use
  ``GIS /usr/people/grass/Grass4.1; export GIS'' and
  ``GISDBASE /usr/people/grass/data; export GISDBASE''.
  Create the directories defined in these environment settings.
  Put all the source code in ``$GIS'', and go to ``$GIS/src/CMD''.
<P>
<DT><STRONG>Things to know</STRONG>
<DD>
  In the Appendix to the installation manual
  you will find some examples of compilation flags for different
  machine architectures or platforms.
  All this information will be stored in a header
  file in the subdirectory 
  ``/usr/people/grass/ Grass4.1/src/CMD/head''.
  The setup of the header file is done by starting ``utils/setup''. 
  This must be done only once. This header file will be 
  used for any future updates. ``gmake4.1'' is the shell script that 
  executes the compilation. The directory where it will
  be placed must be in your path variable.
  The scripts ``GISGEN.$ARCH'' and ``MAKELINKS.$ARCH'' will compile 
  the whole program and link it to the binary directory
  named in the header file.
<P>
<DT><STRONG>IRIX 5.2</STRONG>
<DD>
  While compiling GRASS for IRIX&nbsp;5.2 (Silicon Graphics), problems were
  encountered which even required modifications to the source code!
  This is an example of how much fun
  compilation can be! Support from the GRASS mailing lists
  and newsgroups can be really handy at times like this.
  Simply post a description of the problem to one of the mailing lists
  or newsgroups and someone will be sure to help out.
  In the case of the IRIX problem, a GRASS user (Bill Brown) kindly sent
  some compilation notes (cfr.&nbsp;<A HREF="node69.html#billbrown">8.4</A>).
<P>
<DT><STRONG>Compiling</STRONG>
<DD>
  Once you have created the header file using ``utils/setup'' you will
  see that the different scripts mentioned above are also generated. 
  Now we can select
  the programs we really want to compile, skipping those that aren't of use
  for your application. Go to the subdirectory 
  ``/usr/people/grass/Grass4.1/src/CMD/lists''
  and open the file ``local''.
  Here will be all the programs to be compiled. Some of the drivers
  must be uncommented. Put the specific machine 
  dependent programs and devices in a file ``$ARCH''. This way you can select
  different drivers for different machines, while storing the
  main programs only once. To compile xgrass4.1, 
  concatenate the file ``GRASS.X'' to
  the local file. Now you can start the compilation process. 
  Run the script ``sh GISGEN |&amp; tee /tmp/GISGEN.out''.
  If this should fail, add the option ``-skip'' to skip to the place 
  of failure. If you should need to 
  restart the script, remove the file ``next_step/$ARCH'' first.
  This file contains the name of the last program to have been compiled.
  The ``-skip'' option reads the file that failed and skips it.
  Now you can link everything to the bin directory. Run the script
  ``sh MAKELINKS.$ARCH''.
  For the configuration of the drivers, refer to the installation manual,
  and examine the file
  ``/usr/people/grass/Grass4.1/etc/monitorcap''.
  Finally, if desired, you can delete the object files.
<P>
 </DL><HR><A NAME="tex2html948" HREF="node68.html"><IMG WIDTH=37 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="next" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html946" HREF="node65.html"><IMG WIDTH=26 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="up" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html940" HREF="node66.html"><IMG WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="previous" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/previous_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html950" HREF="node1.html"><IMG WIDTH=65 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="contents" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/contents_motif.gif"></A>  <BR>
<B> Next:</B> <A NAME="tex2html949" HREF="node68.html">Compiling New Modules and </A>
<B>Up:</B> <A NAME="tex2html947" HREF="node65.html">Appendix B: Compiling GRASS</A>
<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME="tex2html941" HREF="node66.html">Downloading the Software</A>
