<BR> <P>
<A NAME="billbrown">&#160;</A><H2><A NAME="SECTION000114000000000000000">Compile Notes for IRIX 5.2 </A></H2>
<P>
(These notes were written by GRASS user Bill Brown)
<P>
When running the setup script I got complaints about some libraries
not being found - just ignore them.  
The script looks for certain
names and can't find them, but cc seems to know to look for the
shared version of the library.
Clearly there were problems to compile i.points, 
i.ortho.photo, i.vpoints. I fixed it by declaring 
the &quot;screen&quot; as a non-static function. Just delete the keyword 
&quot;static&quot; where the function is defined. The following files must be 
changed for that:
src/imagery/i.points/mark.c <BR> 
src.alpha/imagery/i.ortho.photo/photo.2image/mark.c <BR> 
src.alpha/imagery/i.ortho.photo/photo.2target/mark.c <BR> 
src.alpha/imagery/i.vpoints/mark.c
<P>
A few compile problems in xgrass4.1: <BR> 
XCFLAGS = -D_NO_PROTO -DXM_1_1_BC -Umips <BR> 
To compile v.digit , it is needed to remove 
dependancy of menus.o and menus.i from the Gmakefile. There also seems to be a 
problem in v.support. Actually when v.support calls
v.build, get a core dump. It is not clear why this happens but
the best way to avoid this problem is to get the compiled 
version on moon in /grass/incoming/v.build.sgi 
and copy it to GISBASE/etc/v.build.
<P>
This is the head file I used:
<PRE>CC                  = cc 
ARCH                = sgi 
GISBASE             = /usr/people/grass/Grass4.1 
UNIX_BIN            = /usr/people/grass/Grass4.1/bin 
DEFAULT_DATABASE    = /usr/people/grass/data 
DEFAULT_LOCATION    = spearfish 
COMPILE_FLAGS       = -O -cckr 
LDFLAGS             = -s 
XCFLAGS             = -D_NO_PROTO -DXM_1_1_ BC -Umips 
XLDFLAGS            = -lPW 
XINCPATH            = 
XMINCPATH           = 
XLIBPATH            = 
XTLIBPATH           = -L/usr/lib 
XMLIBPATH           = -L/usr/lib 
XLIB                = -lX11 
XTLIB               = -lXt 
XMLIB               = -lXm 
XEXTRALIBS          = -lPW 
TERMLIB             = -ltermlib 
CURSES              = -lcurses $(TERMLIB) 
MATHLIB             = -lm 
#                   LIBRULE = ar ruv $@ $? 
#                   LIBRULE = ar ruv $@ $?; ranlib $@
#                   LIBRULE = ar ruv $@ $?; ar ts $@
#                   LIBRULE = ar rc $@ `lorder $(OBJ)
LIBRULE             = ar ruv $@ $?
USE_TERMIO          = -DUSE_TERMIO
USE_MTIO            = -DUSE_MTIO
USE_FTIME           = 
DIGITFLAGS          = -DUSE_SETREUID -DUSE_SETEUID -DUSE_SETPRIORITY
VECTLIBFLAGS        =
GETHOSTNAME         = -DGETHOSTNAME_OK
XDRLIB = -lsun</PRE>
<P>
<BR> <HR>
