<head><title>GIS links</title> </head>
<BODY VLINK="#ff0000" LINK="ffff00" bgcolor="42426f" TEXT="ffffff">

<h2> 
Some Information About GIS </h2>
<P><HR><P>

<h3> Introductory Reading </h3>
<ul>
   <li>A general <a href="http://info.er.usgs.gov/research/gis/title.html">introduction </a>
   <li>A list of <a href="http://www.census.gov/geo/gis/faq-index.html">Frequently 
   Asked Questions </a> about GIS
</ul>
<p>

<h3> Tools Used on the Lab</h3>
<ul>
   <li>We are currently working with
   <b><a href="/GIS/gis.html"> GRASS </a></b>
   <li><b><a href="http://www.cecer.army.mil/grass/viz/sg3d.tut.html">SG3d</a></b> is
   an additional tool in GRASS for viewing a data surface in three dimensions 
   (only on <i> Silicon Graphics </i> computers)
 </ul>

<h3> Other GIS Tools </h3>
<ul>
   <li><A HREF="http://www.intergraph.com/">Intergraph</A>
   <li><A HREF="ftp://midget.towson.edu/idrisi/">IDRISI</A>
 </ul>

<h3> Some References </h3>
<ul>
    <li>The <a href="http://info.er.usgs.gov/">USGS home page </a>
    <li> <a href="http://www.census.gov/geo/gis/faq-sources.html">Information </a> 
    about mailing lists, ftp sites, available books and magazines
    <li>A <a href="ftp://gis.queensu.ca/pub/gis/docs/gissites.html"> list </a> 
    of internet GIS and remote sensing sites
  </ul>  

<P><HR><P>
