<HTML VERSION="2.0">
<HEAD>
<!-- WEBMAGIC VERSION NUMBER="2.0.1" -->
<!-- WEBMAGIC TRANSLATION NAME="ServerRoot" SRC="/var/www/htdocs/" DST="/" -->
<!-- WEBMAGIC TRANSLATION NAME="ProjectRoot" SRC="./" DST="" -->
<TITLE>Some info </TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY VLINK="#ff0000" LINK="ffff00" bgcolor="42426f" TEXT="ffffff">
<H2>Some info</H2>
<H3>My job</H3>
<P>Finally after a long period I can go back to the place where I started.
From 1st of septemebr 1995 I work for a project financed by the Flemish
Inter University Council (VLIR) and the Belgian Agency for Collaboration
in Developement (ABOS-AGCD). The project: <A HREF="/projects/VLIR/vlir.html">&quot;Study, Management, Production and Application of Fresh Water and Geothermal
Water and their Use in Horticulture in Tunisia&quot; </A>will try to study the use of Geothermal water and his derivates for use
in cooling and irrigation in horticulture in the Tunisian Sahel </P>
<P><A HREF="/projects/VLIR/ham.jpg"><IMG SRC="/projects/VLIR/hampri.jpg"> </A><A HREF="/projects/VLIR/tow.jpg"><IMG SRC="/projects/VLIR/towpri.jpg"> </A>. </P>
<P>I am still working as scientific colaborator at the Laboratory of Hydrology
and Water Management at <A HREF="http://www.rug.ac.be/">University of Ghent </A>in <A HREF="http://pespmc1.vub.ac.be/BelgCul.html">Belgium </A>. </P>
<P>Before I was working for the ERS1/ERS2 project financed by the DWTC. This
project tries to evaluate the posibilties of deriving soilmoisture from
the active radar instruments on board of the ERS1 sattelite and the recently
launched ERS2 sattelite. Deriving soilmoisture from these images should
allow hydrologists to estimate in a better way intial conditions for their
hydrological models. </P>
<P>Last two years I was also responsable for the computional resources at this
lab. Together with Peter Troch we try to keep our machines in good shape.
I am working as <B>webmaster </B>of our www server and in this way I am responsable for the public relations
of the <A HREF="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/">Laboratory of Hydrology </A>thru internet. </P>
<HR>
<P>Recently I spended 4 months as GIS consultant at <A HREF="http://www.crs4.it/">CRS4 <I></A>(Centro di Ricerca, Sviluppo e Studi Superiori in Sardegna) </I>in <A HREF="http://www.crs4.it/HTML/living_in_cagliari.html">Cagliari </A>on <A HREF="http://www.crs4.it/HTML/~zip/sardinia/esit.html">Sardinia </A>. </P>
<P>Mainly I was working on the application of <A HREF="rep/paper.html">GIS in hydrology </A>. Interesting information on GIS can be found at the the server of <A HREF="http://info.er.usgs.gov/research/gis/title.html">the USGS agency </A>or at the <A HREF="http://www.bae.ncsu.edu:/bae/people/faculty/walker/hotlist.html#Geoscience">GIS-hotlist </A>made by Joe Walker. </P>
<P>One of the few public domain GIS systems is <A HREF="/brows/gis.html">GRASS</A>. originally set up by <A HREF="http://www.cecer.army.mil/">the United States Army Corps of Engineers Construction Engineering Research
Laboratories </A>. </P>
<HR>
<P>My lab is currently working on soil moisture mapping by means of remote
sensed data. Main platforms are <A HREF="http://www.esrin.esa.it/">ERS-1 satelite of ESA </A>; The Shuttle <A HREF="http://hypatia.gsfc.nasa.gov/">(NASA)</A>, and the European Multisensor Airborn Campaign (EMAC). </P>
<P>The Laboratory of Hydrology and Water Management is setting up a GIS project
for the Zwalm catchment in the frame of the IOZ (The Zwalm Research Team)
and the EC-Environment Program. This hydrological testsite is under study
eversince 1991. A network of water quantity and quality stations is set
up during these years. More information about this test site can be grabbed
from my <A HREF="paper/paper.html">final report </A>written at CRS4. </P>
<HR>
<P><BR>
<BLINK><A HREF="cveng.html">More about my curriculum !! </BLINK></A></P>
<HR>
<PRE>
<A HREF="mailto:Bart.Cosyn@rug.ac.be"> <IMG SRC="mailbox.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE" ALT="MAIL" WIDTH="45" HEIGHT="45" SGI_SETWIDTH SGI_SETHEIGHT SGI_FULLPATH="/disk03/usr/people/bart/WWW/mailbox.gif"></A> Any questions about this page? 
</PRE>
