<BR> <P>
<H2><A NAME="SECTION00033000000000000000">GIS at CRS4</A></H2>
<P>
At CRS4, Version&nbsp;4.1 of the public domain GIS software GRASS, 
is currently installed and 
operational on a Silicon Graphics workstation, and will be used
as the main GIS system for the project. 
GRASS4.1 was installed by B. Cosyn in Oct/94, and in subsequent 
months ground truth, digital elevation, and satellite 
data for the Zwalm catchment were obtained
from the Laboratory of Hydrology and Water Management
of the University of Gent, which is the project partner responsible for 
that test site. The collection and organization of data from the
other three test sites is in progress.
<P>
<BR> <HR>
<P><ADDRESS>
<I>Bart Cosyn <BR>
Thu Jul 25 13:19:15 MDT 1996</I>
