<BR> <P>
<H2><A NAME="SECTION00034000000000000000">Summary of the Report</A></H2>
<P>
This report will describe the data of one of the test sites, 
the Zwalm catchment in Belgium. This will serve to give an overview of
the general data to be expected from all test sites 
during the course of the project. 
Chapter&nbsp;<A HREF="node8.html#catalog">2</A> describes the Zwalm test site, 
the setup of the permanent monitoring network at this site, and the
various data types from the site.
An overview of the ground truth campaigns held from April 1994 
to the present is given in Chapter&nbsp;<A HREF="node21.html#campa">3</A>, as well as a
description of the different remote sensing instruments that monitored
the catchment during this period.
<P>
A general description of GRASS is given in Chapter&nbsp;<A HREF="node34.html#Grass">4</A>, and the
GRASS setup for the Zwalm site is described in Chapter&nbsp;<A HREF="node52.html#datagrass">6</A>.
As GRASS was developed in the United States, it contains 
no modules for common European reference systems.
In Chapter&nbsp;<A HREF="node40.html#transgrass">5</A> the Belgian
reference system and the UTM reference system are described, 
together with a solution to the problem of
changing from one projection system to another in GRASS. 
Appendices&nbsp;A and&nbsp;B provide some GRASS scripts
written specifically for the project and instructions 
for obtaining and installing the GRASS software.
<P>
<BR> <HR>
<P><ADDRESS>
<I>Bart Cosyn <BR>
Thu Jul 25 13:19:15 MDT 1996</I>
