<H2><A NAME="SECTION00042000000000000000">Permanent Data of the Zwalm Catchment</A></H2>
<P>
The Laboratory of Hydrology and Water Management (LHWM) at the 
University of Gent owns a collection of permanent
maps mainly used for image processing and field campaign organization. 
These maps
are partially digitized or scanned as raster maps. 
The main layer for hydrologic 
modeling is the digital elevation model (DEM). 
The following section will give an 
overview of available time independent (static) data.
<P><A NAME="1593">&#160;</A><A NAME="demps">&#160;</A><A NAME="tex2htmlfigure1591" HREF="img7.gif"><IMG WIDTH=101 HEIGHT=124 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="figure1590" SRC="Timg7.gif"></A><BR>
<STRONG>Figure 2:</STRONG> DEM of the Zwalm catchment.<BR>
<P><BR> <HR>
<UL> 
<LI> <A NAME="tex2html307" HREF="node13.html#SECTION00042100000000000000">Digital Elevation Map</A>
<LI> <A NAME="tex2html308" HREF="node14.html#SECTION00042200000000000000">Topographic Maps</A>
<LI> <A NAME="tex2html309" HREF="node15.html#SECTION00042300000000000000">Orthofotomaps</A>
<LI> <A NAME="tex2html310" HREF="node16.html#SECTION00042400000000000000">Soil Maps and Soil Properties</A>
</UL>
<BR> <HR>
<P><ADDRESS>
<I>Bart Cosyn <BR>
Thu Jul 25 13:19:15 MDT 1996</I>
</ADDRESS>
