<BR> <P>
<H3><A NAME="SECTION00042200000000000000">Topographic Maps</A></H3>
<P>
Topographic maps of the complete region containing the Zwalm catchment are 
available. A topographic map at scale 1:50000 contains the full catchment.
Detailed 1:25000 topographic maps are also available. 
On Intergraph workstations 10 black and white digitized raster format 
topographic maps are available and will be processed in order to get 
an overall digital topographic raster map.
These maps are mosaiced to get one topographic map at scale 1:10000 of the
whole region. This map is mainly used to allow georeferencing of the
uncoded ERS and J-ERS images. These images can be imported in GRASS using
standard routines. Data will be delivered as raw standard integer products.
<P>
<BR> <HR>
