<BR> <P>
<H2><A NAME="SECTION00051000000000000000">Introduction</A></H2>
<P>
Between April and October 1994 ERS-1 SAR precision
images (PRI) were collected over the Zwalm catchment. These images are first
processed by the Italian Processing and Archiving Facility 
(I-PAF)<A NAME="tex2html6" HREF="footnode.html#1677"><IMG  ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="gif" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/foot_motif.gif"></A>. 
An average of 3 images per month are available&nbsp;[<A HREF="node63.html#zwcol94"><EM>Troch  et al., </EM><EM>Troch  et al.</EM><EM>
  1994</EM></A>]. These images
will be collected by LHWM. Su et al.&nbsp;su94 give 
an overview of the characteristics of the ERS-1 and J-ERS-1 images. 
After processing by I-PAF the images of the Zwalm region will be 
geocoded by LHWM, after which the images will be delivered to CRS4.
<P>
<BR> <HR>
<P><ADDRESS>
<I>Bart Cosyn <BR>
Thu Jul 25 13:19:15 MDT 1996</I>
</ADDRESS>
</BODY>
