<H3><A NAME="SECTION00053400000000000000">Vegetation Characteristics</A></H3>
<P>
The same metal plate used for surface roughness measurements is used to 
estimate certain vegetation characteristics for non-bare soil fields. 
In the case of row structure (i.e. winter
wheat or maize), slides are taken along and across the rows, allowing 
the determination of row distance, distance in the row, and plant density 
(number of plants per m <IMG WIDTH=6 HEIGHT=9 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2775" SRC="img5.gif"  > ). Plant
height is also easily determined from the slides. For pasture fields only grass 
height is derived from the slides.
<P>
On June 16 and June 30 plants were collected and stored in airtight 
plastic bags. They were then used to determine the leaf area index (LAI). 
Unfortunately, many samples from June 30 were destroyed because 
of the delay between harvesting and analysis.
<P><A NAME="1721">&#160;</A><A NAME="reflectors">&#160;</A> <IMG WIDTH=365 HEIGHT=171 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="table1720" SRC="img46.gif"  > <BR>
<STRONG>Table 3:</STRONG> Position of the Corner Reflectors for the EMAC Campaign, April 1994<BR>
<P><BR> <HR>
