 <A NAME="tex2html577" HREF="node36.html"><IMG WIDTH=37 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="next" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html575" HREF="node34.html"><IMG WIDTH=26 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="up" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html569" HREF="node34.html"><IMG WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="previous" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/previous_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html579" HREF="node1.html"><IMG WIDTH=65 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="contents" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/contents_motif.gif"></A>  <BR>
<B> Next:</B> <A NAME="tex2html578" HREF="node36.html">How to Introduce Yourself </A>
<B>Up:</B> <A NAME="tex2html576" HREF="node34.html">The Use of GRASS</A>
<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME="tex2html570" HREF="node34.html">The Use of GRASS</A>
<BR> <P>
<H2><A NAME="SECTION00061000000000000000">What is GRASS?</A></H2>
<P>
The geographical resources analysis support system (GRASS)
is a geographic information system developed by the U.S. Army's
Construction Engineering Research Laboratories (USA-CERL). GRASS can be
used for preparing geographical data obtained from other systems, for
processing and analyzing geographical data, and for
basic visualization of geographical data.
For some of these jobs,
functionality from other public domain software packages
(for example RIM, gnuplot, gctp and PBMplus) is used.
Scripts can be written for well defined jobs that need be
performed repeatedly.
<P>
The current version is GRASS4.1 and is available in the public
domain. On the server where GRASS resides one can also find
tutorials, manuals, and references, both from the GRASS developers and from
people currently working with the system.
GRASS is used world wide, and the user base includes
programmers who create new GRASS modules to perform additional functionality.
New modules and new releases of old modules are posted on the GRASS server.
<P>
GRASS handles data in raster, vector and point format and is primarily intended
to work with UTM coordinates. The main limitation is that the system
only supports processing of data at one of the 60 UTM
zones at a time&nbsp;[<A HREF="node63.html#grassref93"><EM>CERL, </EM><EM>CERL</EM><EM>1993</EM>b</A>, <A HREF="node63.html#grassbeg93"><EM>Van&nbsp;Leusen, </EM><EM>Van&nbsp;Leusen</EM><EM>
  1993</EM></A>].
It also handles Geographic coordinates in a
limited way (some tools do not accept this projection).
<P>
GRASS is often used as an exchange GIS system and includes basic conversions
to other GIS formats. Because of the way UNIX shells and environment
variables are used, it is easy for the user to
set the environment according the needs of each project separately.
Although GRASS is command line driven and somewhat user unfriendly,
it has the advantage of being easily linked with locally created programs.
<P>
The main GRASS4.1 system is extended with the following additional components:
<DL ><DT><STRONG>Imagery</STRONG>
<DD>
   Imagery includes a pointer driven georeferencing program, some basic
   reclassification algorithms, and filtering procedures. Filtering procedures
   can easily be programmed by means of the mapcalc program that provides a
   tool for basic array mathematics.
<DT><STRONG>Mapdev</STRONG>
<DD>
   Mapdev provides input from and output to  peripheral hardware like
   digitizers, printers, and plotters.
<DT><STRONG>Data base management systems (DBMS)</STRONG>
<DD>
   Links exist to the public domain database management system RIM, and GRASS
   may also be used in conjunction with commercial DBMSs like Informix
   and Oracle.
<DT><STRONG>X-GRASS</STRONG>
<DD> 
   USA-CERL has started to develop a menu-driven 
   version of GRASS for X-windows called xgrass4.1.
<P>
 </DL><HR><A NAME="tex2html577" HREF="node36.html"><IMG WIDTH=37 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="next" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html575" HREF="node34.html"><IMG WIDTH=26 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="up" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html569" HREF="node34.html"><IMG WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="previous" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/previous_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html579" HREF="node1.html"><IMG WIDTH=65 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="contents" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/contents_motif.gif"></A>  <BR>
