 <A NAME="tex2html599" HREF="node38.html"><IMG WIDTH=37 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="next" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html597" HREF="node34.html"><IMG WIDTH=26 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="up" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html591" HREF="node36.html"><IMG WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="previous" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/previous_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html601" HREF="node1.html"><IMG WIDTH=65 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="contents" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/contents_motif.gif"></A>  <BR>
<B> Next:</B> <A NAME="tex2html600" HREF="node38.html">GRASS from the Shell</A>
<B>Up:</B> <A NAME="tex2html598" HREF="node34.html">The Use of GRASS</A>
<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME="tex2html592" HREF="node36.html">How to Introduce Yourself </A>
<BR> <P>
<H2><A NAME="SECTION00063000000000000000">The GRASS File Structure</A></H2>
<P>
GRASS includes executable files, libraries, drivers for
external devices, scripts, fonts, locking capabilities,
online help, and manual pages. The organization of these components, and
also of user data, is
done within the UNIX file system, as shown in Figure&nbsp;<A HREF="node37.html#projgrass">3</A>.
<P>
The main subdivisions in a GRASS data base
are ``locations'', which define the possible
active regions. Each region has to be at least bigger than the biggest area
imported into the location.
The ``mapset'' allows the user to define subregions, and restricts
the user to the working area defined in the location.
All the appropriate subdirectories are placed
under the mapset directory. The naming convention for the subdirectories
depends on the type of data. For instance, binary raster files (without
the headers) are placed in the subdirectory ``cell'', the headers
from binary raster files are places in the subdirectory ``cellhd'', etc.
<P><A NAME="1979">&#160;</A><A NAME="projgrass">&#160;</A><A NAME="tex2htmlfigure1977" HREF="img50.gif"><IMG WIDTH=229 HEIGHT=264 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="figure1976" SRC="Timg50.gif"></A><BR>
<STRONG>Figure 3:</STRONG> Directory layout of GRASS and a GRASS database.<BR>
<P><BR> <HR>
