<B> Next:</B> <A NAME="tex2html719" HREF="node48.html">GRASS and the Different </A>
<B>Up:</B> <A NAME="tex2html717" HREF="node45.html">Reference Systems and Projections </A>
<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME="tex2html713" HREF="node46.html">Reference Systems</A>
<BR> <P>
<H3><A NAME="SECTION00073200000000000000">Map Projections</A></H3>
<P>
For the Zwalm catchment LHWM
uses a common system for Belgium, Lambert72. 
This local system was selected since most of the maps produced in
Belgium use Lambert72, and thus the task of
digitizing the many different maps is facilitated.
For a more internationally recognized reference and projection system,
UTM was selected. GRASS fully supports this projection.
<DL ><DT><STRONG>Lambert72</STRONG>
<DD>
  A conformic conic projection with two parallel circles 
  with the following characteristics:  <IMG WIDTH=97 HEIGHT=31 ALIGN=MIDDLE ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2955" SRC="img53.gif"  > ,
   <IMG WIDTH=97 HEIGHT=31 ALIGN=MIDDLE ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2957" SRC="img54.gif"  > .
  The central meridian goes through  <IMG WIDTH=155 HEIGHT=30 ALIGN=MIDDLE ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2959" SRC="img55.gif"  > .
<P>
  <DT><STRONG>Universal Transverse Mercator (UTM)</STRONG>
<DD>
  UTM is a cylindrical transversal projection. The 0-meridian and 
  the equator are projected as straight lines. The reference ellipsoid 
  is usually Hayford. In UTM projections there are 60 identical
  zones of  <IMG WIDTH=16 HEIGHT=14 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2961" SRC="img56.gif"  > . Belgium is almost completely situated in UTM zone&nbsp;31, 
  excepted for the northeast (German border) which is situated in zone&nbsp;32.
  The central meridian goes through  <IMG WIDTH=90 HEIGHT=28 ALIGN=MIDDLE ALT="tex2html_wrap_inline2963" SRC="img57.gif"  > .
  Along the central meridian a scaling factor is used to limit the
  distortion of distances. The conversion equations are the same for all
  60 zones. Knowledge of the central meridian should be sufficient
  to calculate the transformations for all zones.
<P>
 </DL><BR> <HR>
<P><ADDRESS>
<I>Bart Cosyn <BR>
Thu Jul 25 13:19:15 MDT 1996</I>
</ADDRESS>
