 <A NAME="tex2html741" HREF="node50.html"><IMG WIDTH=37 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="next" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/next_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html739" HREF="node48.html"><IMG WIDTH=26 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="up" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/up_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html733" HREF="node48.html"><IMG WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="previous" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/previous_motif.gif"></A> <A NAME="tex2html743" HREF="node1.html"><IMG WIDTH=65 HEIGHT=24 ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="contents" SRC="http://taoren.rug.ac.be/lat2html/contents_motif.gif"></A>  <BR>
<B> Next:</B> <A NAME="tex2html742" HREF="node50.html">Transformation of Raster Data </A>
<B>Up:</B> <A NAME="tex2html740" HREF="node48.html">GRASS and the Different </A>
<B> Previous:</B> <A NAME="tex2html734" HREF="node48.html">GRASS and the Different </A>
<BR> <P>
<A NAME="points">&#160;</A><H3><A NAME="SECTION00074100000000000000">Transformation of Points </A></H3>
<P>
In order to be able to transform points from one system to another, a Fortran
code has been written. The code includes four subroutines and
calculates the transformation from Geographic data based on the
European Dat50 (ED50) system to UTM and Belgian Lambert72 coordinates. 
The four subroutines are:
<DL ><DT><STRONG>geotoUTM.f</STRONG>
<DD>  ED50 to UTM zone 31
  <DT><STRONG>UTMtogeo.f</STRONG>
<DD>  UTM zone 31 to ED50
  <DT><STRONG>UTMtolamb.f</STRONG>
<DD> UTM zone 31 to Lambert72
  <DT><STRONG>lambtoUTM.f</STRONG>
<DD> Lambert72 to UTM zone 31
<P>
 </DL>
These subroutines form the main part of the code ``coord''.
The program also includes subroutines to read and write data. 
It forms the basis for further transformation of data within GRASS
from Lambert72 to UTM and vice versa.
<P>
<BR> <HR>
<P><ADDRESS>
<I>Bart Cosyn <BR>
Thu Jul 25 13:19:15 MDT 1996</I>
