<H1><A NAME="SECTION000100000000000000000">Appendix A: GRASS Scripts</A></H1>
<P>
These are the GRASS scripts written specifically for the EC
project. They should provide a good idea of
the possibilities of shell scripting for GRASS.
The scripts are in directory ``/usr/people/grass/Grass4.1/shells''.
<PRE>clfr            clears frames 
cls             clears a single frame display 
createdir       creates all necessary directories in a new mapset 
d.myicons       displays site + icons if name of site and icon are equal 
d.trans.icon    displays transect data with icon
d.trans.labels  displays transect data with labels
d.trans.num     extraction and display of soil moisture data by 
                date and depth 
fa-fd           selects frames a,b,c or d 
fr              creates 2 new vertical frames (50%-50%) 
fr4             creates 4 new vertical frames (25% each) 
i.diff.his      displays 2 images with respective histograms on 1 display 
image.select    a demo for menu use 
iris            selects the SGI display 
s.to.label      sites to label convertor 
s0-s11          start one of the 12 X-windows displays 
siris           starts an SGI display (only from console) 
stations        demo for quick displaying; Zwalm logging stations 
stopiris        stops the SGI display 
stopx0-stopx11  stop one of the 12 X-displays 
tifftograss     conversion from tiff to 3 raw colorbands .grn, .red, .blu 
x0-x11          select one of the 12 X-displays 
g.news          news from the GRASS manager 
g.scripts       gives an overview of all the scripts delivered by 
                third parties 
d.histo.gnu     shows the histogram of an image thru gnuplot 
d.trans.gnu     shows a histogram of the soil samples thru gnuplot</PRE>
<P>
<BR> <HR>
