<h2>The Tech's New Home</h2>

<table align=right cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>

<tr><td valign=top><a href="/cgi-bin/sitecam.cgi"><img src="/hyper/gb/sitecam.gif" width=320 height=240 border=0 alt="Live image of the construction site"></a></td></tr>
<tr><td align=middle><font size="-1">SiteCam - 

Tue Jan 21 16:58:26 PST 1997

</font></td></tr>
</table>


On June 11th, 1996, The Tech celebrated its <a href="/hyper/gb">groundbreaking</a> for a new facility to open in late 1998.  The new building will include a 1,200 square foot large-screen <a href="http://www.spe.sony.com/Pictures/sonytheatres/imax/imax.html">IMAX</a> Dome Theater with seating capacity for 300; <a href="/hyper/gb/park.html">four main galleries</a> totaling 32,000 square feet of exhibit space; and 3,500 square feet for a hands-on laboratory space for student workshops.  Our projected attendance is 650,000 visitors a year including 130,000 students and teachers.

<table align=left cellpadding=5>
<tr><td valign=top><img src="/newhome/map.gif" width=160 height=221></td></tr>
<tr><td width=160><font size="-1">The blue dome marks the construction site, and the red <font color="#ff0000">X</font> marks the location of the SiteCam.</font></td></tr>
</table>

<br>

Since July, the SiteCam has been capturing images of the new
site to chart our construction progress.
The SiteCam is a small CCD camera located on the 12th floor
of Park Center Plaza, at the corner of Park and Market in downtown San
Jose.  The camera's composite output is
connected to a 2.4 GHz microwave transmitter which beams the signal
directly to our roof via a pair of high-gain antennas hand-crafted by
<a href="mailto:ellery@thetech.org">Ellery Horrilleno</a>, our
resident RF expert.  The receiver unit is connected to the composite video
input on our Web server, an SGI Indy, where the images are archived
and compiled into a <a href="/cgi-bin/sitecam.pl">time-lapse QuickTime movie</a> every hour.

<p>

For updates from the construction site, see the <a href="/cgi-bin/sitecam.cgi">construction log</a>,
brought to you by Barnes Construction in partnership with Turner
Construction.  The Tech also thanks Tarlton Property Management for the use of their
premises.

	  </td>
	</tr>
      </table>

