	  <td valign=top width="75%">
	    <!-- text cell -->
	    <h2>About The Tech</h2>

The Tech is an exciting, hands-on museum of technology and
an educational resource for the Silicon Valley. Find out more
about us on this page, including directions! 

<h2>Directions</h2>

Our address is 145 West San Carlos Street, San Jose, California, 95113.  We are located in downtown San Jose, across the street from the main library and the Convention Center.  <a href="directions.html">Detailed directions are available here</a>.

<h2>Admissions</h2>

The Tech is open Tuesday through Sunday from 10 AM to 5 PM.  Admission is
$6 for adults, and $4 for youths, students and seniors.  <a href="/membership">Members</a> and children 5 and under are free.

<h2>Evening Rentals</h2>

The Tech is available for rentals Monday through Sunday between 6 pm and midnight.  The facility is closed Thanksgiving Day, Christmas Eve and Day, and New Year's Eve and Day.  For more info, <a href="evenings.html">see the evening rental page</a>.

<h2>Employment Opportunities</h2>

The Tech offers competitive salary and excellent benefits including paid
health, dental, and life insurance.  Check our <a href="/hr">job listings</a> page for more information.

<h2>Contact Info</h2>

Please contact us by <a href="contact.html">phone, fax, or e-mail</a> for more information on group visits, evening rentals, membership, donations, or anything else you need to know. 

	  </td>
