	  <td valign=top width="75%">
	    <!-- text cell -->
<h2>Volunteering at The Tech</h2>
Tech volunteers have contributed over 100,000 hours of service, in a variety of different roles.
<h2>We need you!</h2>
We are always looking for volunteers.  Call us at 408-279-7175 for information on how to apply.
<br clear=left>
<h2>Who can volunteer?</h2>

Enthusiastic individuals fifteen years of age and older.  No
technical experience required for most positions.

<h2>How can I help?</h2>
<dl>	
<dt>
<b>
A<font size=-1>DMISSION AND</font>
I<font size=-1>NFORMATION</font>
A<font size=-1>SSISTANT</font><br>
</b>
<dd>
Greet visitors, answer questions, and provide general information
about The Tech Museum of Innovation.<p>
<dt>
<b>
T<font size=-1>ECH</font> S<font size=-1>TORE</font></a>
A<font size=-1>SSISTANT</font><br>
</b>
<dd>
Support the <a href="/techstore.html">Museum Store</a> staff by assisting customers who have questions
and demonstrating store products.<p>
<dt>
<b>
E<font size=-1>XHIBIT</font>
E<font size=-1>XPLAINER</font>
</b>
<dd>
Interpret and explain The Tech <a href="/exhibits.html">exhibits</a> with school groups and the
public, encouraging interaction.<p>

<dt>
<b>
S<font size=-1>PECIAL</font>
L<font size=-1>AB</font>
A<font size=-1>SSISTANT</font><br>
</b>
<dd>
Assist school groups and other visitors to participate in
acitivies featured in one of the three laboratories.<p>

<dt>
<b>
E<font size=-1>XHIBIT</font>
E<font size=-1>NGINEERING</font>
A<font size=-1>SSISTANT</font><br>
</b>
<dd>
Assist with maintaining and modifying the equipment, enhancing the
<a href="/exhibits.html">exhibits</a>.<p>
<br clear=right>
</dl>
<h2>What training will I receive?</h2>

You will be trained by The Tech staff, experienced volunteers, and
industry experts.

<h2>When do you need me?</h2>

<strong>Right now!</strong>  The Tech is open Tuesday through Sunday, 10 am to 5 pm.
Volunteers work either a morning or afternoon session.

<h2>Where do I sign up?</h2>

At The Tech, which is located at <a href="/directions.html">
145 West San Carlos Street</a> in
downtown San Jose.  You can also call our volunteer coordinator at 408-279-7175 for a volunteer application and information sheet, or you can fill out our online <a href="/requests/volunteer-form.html">volunteer application form</a>.

<p>

You can also volunteer to participate in <a href="/wov">Women of Vision</a>, a non-profit volunteer organization founded in 1992 to do educational outreach for The Tech.

	  </td>
	</tr>
      </table>

      <p>
