<body text="#FFFFFF" bgcolor="#000000" link="#FFFFFF" vlink="#FFFFFF"
alink="#FFFFFF">

<center><h2>The New Tech Galleries - Life Tech</h2><img src="inside.gif" border=0></p></center>

<table>
<br clear=left>

<tr>
<td valign=top>
<center><p><img src="lifetech_entry.gif" hspace=20 border=0
align=left>
<br clear=left><i>View of Entry </i></p></center>

<center><p><img src="lifetech_omnimax.gif" hspace=20 border=0 align=left>
<br clear=left><i>View from Omnimax Exit </i></p></center>
</td>

<td width=400><b>LIFE TECH
<br>
<br> Perspective </b>
<p>This area evokes and anticipates the experiences of the Life Tech gallery
through vivid images, kinetic devices, and multisensory interactives. Images
from the exhibit hall appear on overhead screens; a large chromosome sculpture
splits and spirals into the gallery. A touch, step, even breath of a visitor
triggers projected images or sensors to react and move. Each experience
reinforces the concept that Life Tech is about technology, the human body,
and the compelling issues that arise when they merge in medicine, physical
activity, the exploration of physiology, and genetics. </p>

</td>
</tr>
<br clear=left>

</table>

<p>

<b>A New Self Image</b> </p>

<p>This area focuses on the new ways technology allows us to see, hear,
quantify, record, and model the body, changing our &quot;self image&quot;
and expanding our perception of our own body. Exhibits here allow visitors
to understand what different technologies tell us about the workings of
the human body, from brain activity to tissues and structural systems to
cardiopulmonary functions. Each visitor will grasp the implications of
these technologies on a personal level through such experiences as face-aging
simulation, ultrasound imaging of a baby, biofeedback exercises, or simply
measuring their pulse. </p>

<p><b>Life's New Frontiers </b></p>

<p>The nature of the technologies in genetic science is dictated by the
richness and subtlety of life itself. Life's New Frontiers shows how this
intermeshing of technology with the building blocks of life is accomplished
by working in step with and amplifying natural mechanisms and forms. Simple
interactives acquaint visitors with DNA and genetic processes before introducing
the technology and methods used to identify and map the molecular sequences
in genomes. Other exhibits present the applications opened up by such
manipulation
of genetic material, such as new medical therapies or new varieties of
plants and animals. A major thread throughout this area encompasses the
stories of individuals as well as some of the ethical challenges presented
by these new capabilities. </p>

<p><b>Life Support </b></p>

<p>Exhibits here help visitors understand how technology helps analyze
information for diagnoses and how it provides an information resource for
patients and doctors alike. Also, visitors try some of the technologies
that guide practitioners during procedures, or function as extensions of
judgment or the senses. Interactives demonstrate how technology can sometimes
enable the patient to take a stronger role in choosing and participating
in treatments. Technology is expanding and altering the ways we promote
health, prevent disease, and mend the body. Information technologies, new
insights into drug development, action, and delivery, and more finely tuned
methods of treatment have transformed and expanded health care. As advanced
devices become more prevalent their prominence in the relationship of patient
to health care provider increases. With each new medical technology, the
roles of patient and health care provider take on new dimensions. </p>

<p><b>Beyond Our Limits </b></p>

<p>This area focuses on technology's enhancement of physical activity,
from the specialty devices used by world-class athletes, to the everyday
enabling devices that the rest of us might use. Interactives here allow
visitors to try out the latest computer simulations, motion tracking, and
motion analysis devices for improving athletic performance, or try out
how they would do driving a wheelchair around the city. They can immerse
themselves in the protective gear of a professional hockey goalie and see
how well it protects. Throughout, the stories of individual accomplishments
of active people personalize the impact of these new technologies on all
of us. </p>

<hr>
