<center><p>
<hr size=3 width="80%" >
<br><b><font SIZE=+2>The Tech Capital Campaign
<br></font><font SIZE=+1>A Partnership of Vision and
Destiny</font></b></p></center>

<p>The Tech Museum of Innovation began as a dream of visionary members
of the Junior League of Palo Alto (now mid-peninsula). The Tech's mission
is to engage people of all ages and backgrounds in exploring and experiencing
the technologies affecting their lives, and to inspire our youth to become
innovators in the technologies of the future. </p>

<p>When The Tech opened its doors in November 1990, it was <b>The Garage</b>,
a prototype for a major new interactive museum with the goal of capturing
and nurturing for posterity the future-oriented, innovative spirit of Silicon
Valley. </p>

<p>Now after five years of successful operation, The Tech Board of Directors,
in partnership with the Redevelopment Agency of the City of San Jose, starts
construction of a major new facility, The Future Tech. </p>

<p>The Board of Directors of The Tech Museum of Innovation has pledged
to raise $20 million in cash contributions and $20 million of in-kind support
to construct the interactive exhibits, learning stations, labs, and public
programs of The Future Tech. Inspired by early visionaries and a $39 million
grant from the Redevelopment Agency, The Tech Capital Campaign represents
one of the largest public/private partnerships in the region. </p>

<p>The new building, planned to open in 1998, will be located on the corner
of Park Avenue and Market Street, across from the Plaza de Cesar Chavez.
The current facility will be converted to office and shop areas in support
of the new museum. </p>

<p>Over 650,000 people will visit The Future Tech annually. A talented
education and exhibit staff will support an array of visitor experiences
designed to foster exploration and motivation to learn more about new
technologies
shaping our future choices. </p>

<p>The Future Tech will be organized into four thematic areas, all of which
will bring into focus the profound relationship between people and technology.
The four themes are <b><a
href="http://sizzle.thetech.org/hyper/gb/innov.html">Innovation</a>,
<a href="http://sizzle.thetech.org/hyper/gb/explor.html">Explorations</a>,
<a href="http://sizzle.thetech.org/hyper/gb/comm.html">Communications and
Information</a>, and <a
href="http://sizzle.thetech.org/hyper/gb/lifetech.html">Life
Tech</a>. </b></p>

<p>The educational program of The Future Tech also will include: </p>

<p><b>Omnimax Theater</b></p>

<p>With the most advanced projection system in the world, the sound is
enveloping and the image large and encompassing, making visitors feel a
part of the action. </p>

<p><b>Public Programs</b></p>

<p>Engaging educational experiences include demonstrations, theme weeks,
special events, lectures and on-line access. </p>

<p><b>Programs for Schools and Youth Groups</b></p>

<p>Designed to encourage tomorrow's innovators, these include special courses,
formal labs, professional development programs for teachers, and outreach
activities such as science clubs for schools. </p>

<p><b>Programs for Business and Industry</b></p>

<p>Covering a wide range of interactive events, these include seminars
and symposia, product launches, book signings, technical sessions, family
programs and social activities. </p>

<p><b>Support Facilities</b></p>

<p>Visitors can look forward to a greatly enlarged Museum Store, cafe and
dramatic spaces for evening events. </p>

<p>
<hr size=3 width="80%" ></p>

<center><p><b><font SIZE=+1>Progress Towards Our Goal</font></b></p></center>

<center><p><b><font SIZE=+1>T</font>he Founders Forum</b></p></center>

<p>A distinguished group of industry professionals and community leaders
guides the The Tech Capital Campaign. The Founders Forum provides focus
for Campaign planning and expertise to develop educational programs and
exhibits. </p>

<p>William R. Hewlett, Honorary Chairman</p>

<p>&quot;<i>Let me say The Tech is everything I expected and beyond.</i>&quot;
</p>

<p>David Packard, Senior Advisor</p>

<p>&quot;<i>The Tech is going to be one of the best centers of technology
in the world, and we're going to help make it that way.</i>&quot; </p>

<p>Michael L. Hackworth, Chair, Campaign Cabinet</p>

<p>&quot;<i>The Tech reaches young people early enough in their education
to make a difference. We want our students and future innovators to be
competitive with the best of the best.</i>&quot; </p>

<p>Ray S. AbuZayyad, Chair, Major Gifts</p>

