<center><p><b><font SIZE=+1>The Building</font></b></p></center>

<p>&quot;<i>(The new building) will be an indispensable anchor. It will
give focus to the city in the mind's eye. Like the Eiffel Tower or the
Statue of Liberty, it will be an image that you can retrieve in a split
second. It embodies the thrill of a real city. It will be a building worth
going downtown to see.</i>&quot; </p>

<p>Alan Hess
<br>San Jose Mercury News
<br>July 3, 1994</p>

<p>Internationally acclaimed architect, Ricardo Legorreta, is designing
the building to capitalize on its choice downtown location. The Steinberg
Group of San Jose is the executive architect. </p>

<p>The Future Tech ultimately will include 250,000 square feet. The current
expansion includes 129,000 square feet. The main entrance to the new facility
will be on Market Street, with a secondary entrance on Park Avenue. </p>

<p>The Tech is delighted to be working with a dedicated leadership team,
a world-class architect, and a uniquely qualified group of educators, exhibit
designers and developers to bring The Future Tech to life. </p>
