<title>Exhibits at The Tech</title>
<h1>Bicycles</h1>
The familiar bicycle has been influenced by the technology and materials
of the aerospace industry.  Today's bicycle is customized to fit the 
rider and the location of the ride.  The shape, materials, and accessories
are driven by aerodynamic and weight saving principles.  The exhibit also
shows the power of the computer in industry to connect the usually
separate efforts of product design, manufacturing, and marketing.<p>
<hr>
<img src="/gifs/exhibits/bicycles-2.gif" alt="[For a digitized picture of the Bicycles
exhibit, contact webmaster@thetech.org.]">
<hr>
<img src="/gifs/logos/tech/techbutton-footer.gif" alt="">
<address>The Bicycles Exhibit / The Tech /
<a href="/webmaster.html">webmaster@thetech.org</a></address>
</DOC>
