<title>Exhibits at The Tech</title>
<h1>Biotechnology</h1>
Biotechnology is the science of using living organisms to improve the
quantity or quality of products.  It combines the ideas and needs of
biology and medicine with engineering.<p>
As we discover more about the genetic code, we have increasing power
to influence the development of plants, animals, and people to get a
desired outcome, such as plants that can be made to kill bugs instead
of the bugs killing the plants.  New programs like the Human Genome
Project, intend to identify the location of all human genes and
provide new answers to old questions.  The new biology also raises
important but difficult ethical questions.  The visitor to the
biotechnology exhibit can learn how today's technology allows us to
control the way things grow and develop.<p>
<hr>
<img src="/gifs/exhibits/dna_helix-2.gif" alt="[For a digitized picture of the
Biotechnology exhibit, contact webmaster@thetech.org.]">
<hr>
<img src="/gifs/logos/tech/techbutton-footer.gif" alt="">
<address>The Biotechnology Exhibit / The Tech /
<a href="/webmaster.html">webmaster@thetech.org</a></address>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT10-B17-251</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA086-000617-B013-3</DOCOLDNO>
