<title>Exhibit at The Tech</title>
<h1>Materials</h1>
Today's technology allows us to create new materials by rearranging
things at the molecular level.  We can make ceramics less brittle and
metals more flexible or invent new materials that will behave in a
specific, predetermined way.  But we have to be aware of how and what
we create affects the environment.  Visitors to the materials exhibit
learn first hand how we can create special materials that have
properties we never believed possible before - from soft cloth that
can keep out a bullet to plastic that conducts electricity.<p>
<hr>
<img src="/gifs/logos/tech/techbutton-footer.gif" alt="">
<address>The Materials Exhibit / The Tech /
<a href="/webmaster.html">webmaster@thetech.org</a></address>
</DOC>
