<title>Exhibit at The Tech</title>
<h1>Microelectronics</h1>
The invention of the integrated circuit has had a dramatic impact on
the way we live and the things we use every day.  The making of a chip
is a unique and complex process that happens in a highly controlled
environment.  As the chips themselves and the products they control
get smaller and smaller, the miniaturization raises new challenges
about their manufacture and capabilities in the future.  The visitor
to the microelectronics exhibit can see big things made little, and
little things made big.<p>
<hr>
<img src="/gifs/exhibits/bigchip-2.gif" alt="[For a digitized picture of The Big Chip,
contact webmaster@thetech.org.]">
<hr>
<img src="/gifs/logos/tech/techbutton-footer.gif" alt="">
<address>The Microelectronics Exhibit / The Tech /
<a href="/webmaster.html">webmaster@thetech.org</a></address>

