<title>Exhibits at The Tech</title>
<h1>The Big Chip</h1>
A nine foot square, interactive version of Intel's 486 microprocessor chip
shows people how a chip works.  Visitors can use a touch screen to ask
the chip a specific question and follow the flow of information as
various parts light up, while the chip works in slow motion to answer
the question.<p>
<img src="/gifs/exhibits/bigchip-2.gif" alt="[For a digitized picture of
The Big Chip, contact webmaster@thetech.org.]">
<hr>
<img src="/gifs/logos/tech/techbutton-footer.gif" alt="">
<address>The Big Chip / The Tech /
<a href="/webmaster.html">webmaster@thetech.org</a></address>
