<title>Exhibits at The Tech</title>
<h1>Robotics</h1>
Robots have great strength, reliability, and precision, but they are
not as flexible as human beings nor are they yet as anthropomorphic or
intelligent as they have been portrayed in the movies for the last
forty years.  Engineers have learned to make machines that can do
simple tasks that are too boring, dangerous, or expensive for people
to do.  The next frontier will be the development of more
sophisticated personal service machines.  The visitor to the robot
exhibit is able to interact with five different robots that each
demonstrate a specific ability or application.<p>
<hr>
<img src="/gifs/exhibits/robot_wall-2.gif" alt="[For a digitized picture of The
Robot Wall, contact webmaster@thetech.org.]">
<hr>
<img src="/gifs/logos/tech/techbutton-footer.gif" alt="">
<address>The Robot Wall / The Tech /
<a href="/webmaster.html">webmaster@thetech.org</a></address>
