<html>
<head>
<title>The Tech Museum Store On-Line!</title>
</head>
<body background="/images/bg/space/space.gif" TEXT="#ffffff" LINK="#a8a8a8" vlink="#a8a8a8" alink="#a8a8a8">
<basefont size=3>
<center>
<img src="/images/icons/Tech.gif" alt="">
<h1>The Tech Museum Store On-Line!</h1>
</center>
<blockquote>
The Tech Museum Store is a place where you can find the unexpected--high-tech
gifts, gadgets and clever devices, books, videos, and special publications.
<p>
On this page are just a few of the fun and educational items we have in The
Tech Museum Store.  If you have any questions or would like information
on other store items, please e-mail
<a href="mailto:dennis@thetech.org">Dennis Godward</a>.
<p>
The Tech Museum Store is located inside the main lobby of <a 
href="/directions.html">The Tech Museum</a>, across from
<i>Cafe Tech</i>.
<p>
Consider <a href="/membership">becoming a member</a> when ordering,
which entitles you to a 15% discount on regularly priced merchandise while 
also <a href="http://www.thetech.org/">supporting The Tech</a>!
</blockquote>
<hr>
<font size="+1">
<h2>One-of-a-kind items</h2>
<ul>
<li>Silicon chunks, wafers and jewelry
<li>High-tech clipboards and binders made from motherboards
<li>Science and technology related videos and books
<li>Laser holograms:
<ul><li>Matte and ready to frame
    <li>Or display on an acrylic stand
    <li>Stickers
    <li>Keychains
    <li>Bookmarks
</ul>
<li>Badges with light-emitting diodes and jewelry from computer parts
</ul>
<h2>Fun things to play with</h2>
<ul>
<li>Puzzles and high-tech playing cards 
<li>Novelty items and toys such as:
<ul><li>Miniature Etch-A-Sketch on a keychain
    <li>Stress-measuring cards
    <li>"Crackling Balls"
    <li>Assorted gliding eyeballs
    <li>"Bloom Balls" with suction cups
    <li>Glow-in-the-dark dough
    <li>Disappearing coin bank
    <li>"Roomerang" the indoor boomerang
    <li>Hand Boilers
</ul>
<li>Lego assembly learning kits (originally available only to schools)
<li>Science labs and kits
</ul>
<h2>Customized gifts</h2>
<ul>
<li>T-shirts, mugs, buttons, and more!
</ul>
<center>
<h2>Truly Magnetic!</h2>
<blockquote>
Thousands of years ago it was accidentally discovered that pieces of
certain grayish rock would cling to the point of a spear.  Try one of
our fun explorations in magnets!
</blockquote>
</center>
<hr><p>
<h2>Science With Magnet Kit</h2>
With this kit your child (recommended for
ages 5 to 13) can perform dozens of exciting magnet activities.<p>
<b>Magnet Kit #3976 $12.95</b>
<hr><p>
<h2>Explorabook</h2><img src="/images/store/Explorabook.gif" alt="" align=right hspace=40 vspace=10>
By John Cassidy and the 
<a href="http://www.exploratorium.edu/">Exploratorium</a><br>
A Kid's Science Museum in a book! This wonderful book which won the Parents 
Choice Award of 1992, contains more than 50 activities plus the tools to do 
nearly all of them.  All you need to supply is the world around you and a 
little curiosity about what makes it tick! Recommended for ages 8 to 13.
<br clear=right>
<b>Explorabook #2550 $17.95</b>
<hr>
<h2>Rogers Connection</h2><img src="/images/store/Rogers_Connection.gif" alt="" align=left hspace=40 vspace=10>
A magnetic sculpture toy that comes with recycled
plastic tubes with high power magnets and nickel-plated steel balls
for you to create many unusual shapes and designs. Recommended for ages 7 
to adult.
<br clear=left>
<b>Rogers Connection 15 Tubes and 8 balls #4338 $22.00<br>
Rogers Connection 30 Tubes and 14 balls #4337 $36.00</b>
<hr>
<h2>Tensegritoy</h2><img src="/images/store/Tensegritoy.gif" alt="" align=right hspace=40 vspace=10>
Discover an amazing way to build over 100 different designs that will
demonstrate advanced principles of structure in engineering, physics
and geometry.  This product will transform your child's geometry class
into natural forms from atoms to galaxies!  Turn your imagination
loose!  Recommended for ages 10 to adult.
<br clear=right>
<b>Tensegritoy #3668 $29.95</b>
<hr>
<h2>Official Astronaut Food</h2><img src="/images/store/Astronaut_Food.gif" alt="" align=left hspace=40 vspace=10>
As the Space Shuttle circles the earth, experience similar food as the
astronauts are eating in orbit!  Try tasty Cheese Pizza or Ice Cream.
<br clear=left>
<b>Cheese Pizza #3689 $1.98<br>
Ice Cream #2009 $1.95</b>
<hr>
<h2>Polygonzo</h2><img src="/images/store/Polygonzo.gif" alt="" align=right hspace=40 vspace=10>
Fun for all ages. Intuitively create fanciful designs, or explore deep
spatial principles and universal geometries.  Complete instructions
for the beginner and advanced concepts for the enthusiast of spatial
transformations.  Great for travel!
<br clear=right>
<b>Polygonzeo #3669 $9.95</b>
<hr>
<h2>Orbiter</h2><img src="/images/store/Orbiter.gif" alt="" align=left hspace=40 vspace=10>
Watch the orbiter flash a dazzling colorburst and change its shape as
you demonstrate centrifugal force with this toy of the future!
<br clear=left>
<b>Orbiter #2165 $5.75</b>
<hr>
<h2>Back Spin</h2><img src="/images/store/Backspin.gif" alt="" align=right hspace=40 vspace=10>
This is a puzzle with a new spin!  The idea is simple: place the
colored balls into their matching colored slots.  Beware!  You will
need a strategy to resolve Back Spin.
<br clear=right>
<b>Back Spin #2057 $11.95</b>
<hr>
<h2>Brick-by-Brick</h2><img src="/images/store/Brick_by_Brick.gif" alt="" align=left hspace=40 vspace=10>
This fun five piece puzzle will test your limits!  To play
Brick-by-Brick you combine the five pieces to form patterns that
either you create or try one of the shapes included in the puzzle
deck.  Puzzle enthusiasts and mathematicians like this puzzle because
the rules are simple and complete but lead to a wealth of
possibilities!  Recommended for ages 8 to adult.
<br clear=left>
<b>Brick-by-Brick #3177 $7.95</b>
<hr>
<h2>Mugs and Mice</h2><img src="/images/store/Mugs_and_Mice.gif" alt="" align=right hspace=40 vspace=10>
How about a mug or mouse pad for your desk from The Tech Museum of
Innovation.  Something to remind you of your last exciting visit!
<br clear=right>
<b>The Tech Mug #2544 $4.75<br>
The Tech Mouse Pad #3828 $4.50</b>
<hr>
</font>
<p>
<center>
<a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/iconbar"><img src="/images/icons/iconbar.gif" width=297 height=33 alt="" ismap border=0></a>
<font size=2>
<p><i>Send comments
to <a href="mailto:webmaster@thetech.org"><i>webmaster@thetech.org</i></a>
<p>The Tech Museum of Innovation<br>
145 West San Carlos Street<br>
San Jose, CA, 95113, USA</i>
</font>
</center>
