<h2>The Tech 10: The Tech Museum's monthly catalog of Top High-Tech Web
Sites</H2>

<P>
SAN JOSE, CA (Dec. 21) - School children, teachers, and parents will no
longer face the problem of being all wired up with no place to go.
<P>
To find a neat package of the most exciting, engaging, and useful
technology sites on the World Wide Web, they need only tap into the Tech
Museum of Innovation's "Tech 10"  (<a
href="http://www.thetech.org/hyper/tech10">http://www.thetech.org/hyper/tech10</a>). Although there are numerous "web ratings" sites out there, only The
Tech 10 focuses on high technology for a middle school and above audience.
<P>
The Tech 10 is updated monthly by a team of teachers, students, and museum
staff. Once selected, the winning site can wear the Tech Ten award of
distinction. It also receives a link directly from the Tech's web site, and
is put in The Tech 10 archive for later visits.
<P>
"With schools putting the emphasis on getting wired there's a real need for
educational content out there, to take full advantage of the Web's
capabilities," Peter Giles, president of the Tech. "The Tech as an
institution is filtering through the information to make science and
technology literacy fun and engaging."
<P>
As an added bonus for checking out the site, The Tech 10 offers the Tech 10
Puzzler. A mix between a traditional crossword and an Internet scavenger
hunt, online visitors must visit each of the Tech 10 winners of the month
to find the clues and solve the puzzle. Successful surfers can enter their
name in The Tech 10 Hall of Fame.
<P>
The Tech's web site at (<a
href="http://www.thetech.org/">http://www.thetech.org/</a>)  already offers
a wealth of educational material in HyperTech, its  interactive, online
high-tech museum. Visitors to the site will find virtual exhibits on color,
robotics, earthquakes, DNA, lasers, and Internet privacy.
<P>
<h2>About The Tech</h2>
<P>
The Tech Museum of Innovation is located at 145 W. San Carlos St. in
downtown San Jose. Admission is $6 for adults; $4 for youths, seniors and
students. Members and children 5 and under are free. The museum is open
Tuesday-Sunday 10 a.m.-5 p.m., and Mondays, Dec. 23 and 30, during the
Holidays.
For general information, call (408) 279-7150
or visit <a href="http://www.thetech.org">http://www.thetech.org</a>.

<p>

For more information, please contact:

<p>

Gloria Chun Hoo<br>
Marketing Manager, The Tech Museum of Innovation<br>
(408) 279-7157<br>
<a href="mailto:gloria@thetech.org">gloria@thetech.org</a>


