<h2>Kids Can Call Santa at The Tech
 Using New Video Phone Technology</H2>

<P>
SAN JOSE, CA (Nov. 15) - Kids who aren't thrilled about sitting on Santa
Claus' lap to tell him their holiday wishes will find a better way at The
Tech Museum of Innovation.
<P>
As the holiday season approaches, The Tech is introducing a new exhibit
that mixes the latest in PC video phone technology with the oldest of
family holiday traditions. During regular museum hours beginning Friday,
Nov. 29, kids and family members can call Santa from a kiosk with a home PC
equipped with the new Intel Video Phone technology. Kids will see and talk
to Santa Claus live on the PC screen.
<P>
"We think this will be a huge hit with the kids, especially the younger
ones," said Peter Giles, president of The Tech. "Here is an example of
technology making a difference in our lives. Many small children who are
frightened of talking to a live Santa Claus are not afraid to talk to Santa
on the computer. Talking to Santa at the North Pole on the video phone,
perhaps while sitting on mom's lap, will provide a more comfortable setting
to convey their Christmas wishes."
<P>
The holiday kiosk includes a Quantex Pentium processor-based PC with the
new Intel Video Phone with new ProShare technology.  Using standard analog
phone lines, any phone call can become a video phone call by turning on a
home PC with this technology and selecting this application.
Intel spokeswoman Lorie Wigle said this type of videoconference technology
is taking consumers by storm.
<P>
"Grandparents, children, college students - this technology appeals to
everyone," she said. "The Intel Video Phone is easy to use and allows
people to see each other over regular telephone lines. The video phone
technology is now available in home PCs from Quantex and other major home
PC vendors."
<P>
<P>
<h2>About The Tech</h2>
<P>
The Tech Museum of Innovation is located at 145 W. San Carlos St. in
downtown San Jose. Admission is $6 for adults; $4 for youths, seniors and
students. Members and children 5 and under are free. The museum is open
Tuesday-Sunday 10 a.m.-5 p.m. For general information, call (408) 279-7150
or visit <a href="http://www.thetech.org">http://www.thetech.org</a>.

<p>

For more information, please contact:<br>
Gloria Chun Hoo- The Tech Museum of Innovation<br>
(408) 279-7157 <a href="mailto:gloria@thetech.org">gloria@thetech.org</a><br>

