<h2>MacMurtrie's Frolicsome Robots
Return to The Tech Nov. 21</H2>

<P>
SAN JOSE, CA (Nov. 4) - They may be clunky, they may be preposterous, but
they certainly are endearing.
<P>
The Amorphic Robot Works <font size=-1>(tm)</font size> will return to The
Tech Museum of Innovation for
"Chico MacMurtrie - A Dance of Robots" on Thursday, Nov. 21, at 7 p.m. The
series is underwritten by <a href="http://www.lockheed.com">Lockheed-Martin
Missiles & Space</a> and focuses on the merging of art and technology.
<P>
Tickets for MacMurtrie's performance will be available at the door for $6
and for $5 for museum members. Doors will open at 6 p.m. and the museum
will be open.
<P>
The Tech Museum's recent groundbreaking was stunning, thanks to McMurtrie's
programmed troupe. MacMurtrie's amazing artistry has been described as the
combination of high tech computerized kinetics and electronics with the
quintessential low tech garage mechanic tinkerings and inventions.
In a program immensely popular with people of all ages, MacMurtrie uses
motion, lighting, sound and the choreographed actions of his robotic forms
during his discussion on anthropomorphic, kinetic sculpture.
<P>
MacMurtrie's frolicsome robots, just back from a tour of Europe, will be
the third program in the fall "Art of Technology" series. The fall Tech
Talks series will conclude with "Hal's Legacy ... Beyond 2001: A Space
Odyssey" on Tuesday, Dec. 10, at 7 p.m. Author Dr. David G. Stork will
discuss his newly released book "Hal's Legacy," which explores the
relationship between science fiction and technological fact. His book is
based on the 1968 movie "2001: A Space Odyssey."

<P>

<h2>About The Tech</h2>
<P>
The Tech Museum of Innovation is located at 145 W. San Carlos St. in
downtown San Jose. Admission is $6 for adults; $4 for youths, seniors and
students. Members and children 5 and under are free. The museum is open
Tuesday-Sunday 10 a.m.-5 p.m. For general information, call (408) 279-7150
or visit <a href="http://www.thetech.org">http://www.thetech.org</a>.

<p>

For more information, please contact:

<p>

Gloria Chun Hoo<br>
Marketing Manager, The Tech Museum of Innovation<br>
(408) 279-7157<br>
<a href="mailto:gloria@thetech.org">gloria@thetech.org</a>


