<img src="/images/ui/redbar.gif" alt="" border=0>
<blockquote>
<p><b>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</b><p>
CONTACT:<p>

Heather Gallwas, Microsoft - (415) 573-4976<br>
Leilani Serrecchia, San Jose Clash - (408) 241-9922<br>

<p>
</blockquote>

<p>
<h3>Area organizations team up to give kids more access to technology</h3>
<b>SAN JOSE, CA. (Aug. 5, 1996)</b> -
The Tech Museum of Innovation, the
San Jose Clash soccer team and the local office of Microsoft Corp. will
"kick off" the national debut of Microsoft's free Internet Explorer 3.0
browser through a variety of events that will raise money for the museum.
<p>
        To help raise money for The Tech, Internet users can download IE
3.0 for free by visiting the following web sites and selecting the IE 3.0
button: <a href="http://www.thetech.org/">www.thetech.org</a>, <a href="http://www.clash.com/">www.clash.com</a>, <a href="http://www.kpix.com/">www.KPIX.com</a>,
<a href="http://www.microsoft.com/usa/norcal/">www.microsoft.com/USA/NorCal/</a>. Microsoft will donate a dollar per download
to The Tech up to a total of $20,000.
<p>
        To mark the IE 3.0 debut, kids accompanied by a parent will receive
free admission to The Tech Aug. 13-20. [<a href="ms-note_8-20-96.html">This offer has been extended through Saturday, Aug. 24</a>.]  They also can gain free admission to
the museum through Sept. 30 by bringing a Clash ticket stub from the Aug.
22, Aug. 25 or Sept. 1  games at Spartan Stadium.
<p>
        "This collaboration supports The Tech's goal of making the
innovation and entrepreneurial culture of Silicon Valley available to large
numbers of young children," Tech President Peter Giles said. "We're pleased
to partner with our new Major League Soccer team and Microsoft. We want to
inspire children who are motivated to learn about science and technology
and the opportunities of today and tomorrow."
<p>
        In addition, Microsoft is making a longterm commitment to donate to
The Tech copies of all future releases of Microsoft products for use either
in its exhibits or  educational programs or for administrative use.
<p>
        "We are very pleased that Microsoft has given us in the Bay Area
the autonomy to fund local partners and make a positive impact on the
community we live in," said Joe Fabris, Microsoft's Northern California and
Western Region marketing manager. "Partnering with The Tech and the Clash
is a great way to make sure kids and families see the Internet as
accessible to all."

<h3>About the Clash</h3>
        The Clash and Major League Soccer have provided San Jose with the
chance to witness some of America's and the world's best players performing
the on-field magic that made them international superstars. (Clash to
supply more info here....)

<h3>About The Tech</h3>

        The Tech Museum of Innovation's mission is to engage people of all
ages and backgrounds in exploring and experiencing the technologies
affecting their lives, and to inspire young people to become innovators in
developing the technologies of the future.
<p>
        Through Labor Day, the museum is open Monday-Saturday 10 a.m. to 6
p.m. and Sundays noon to 6 p.m. After Labor Day weekend, the museum's hours
will be Tuesday-Saturday 10 a.m.-5 p.m. and Sundays noon to 5 p.m.

<p>

For information, contact:<br>
Heather Gallwas, Microsoft - (415) 573-4976<br>
Leilani Serrecchia, San Jose Clash - (408) 241-9922<br>

