<p>
<h3>Calendar Listings for July-August 1996 at The Tech Museum of Innovation
</h3>
<b>SAN JOSE, CA, July 1, 1996</b> --

<P>
<U><B>JULY 1: New Summer Hours Begin - Tech Open Everyday</B></U>
<P>
July 1 through Labor Day, The Tech will observe new summer hours.
 The Tech will be open Monday-Saturday, 10 am to 6 pm; Sunday,
noon to 6 pm.  (As of September 3, hours will be Tuesday-Saturday,
10 to 5 pm; Sunday, noon to 5 pm.)
<P>
<U><B>Special Exhibit - Lasers, Light &amp; Color </B></U>
<P>
A whirling kaleidoscope of color, light and scientific discovery,
The Tech Museum of Innovation&#146;s  special exhibit, <B>Lasers,
Light &amp; Color, </B> allows visitors to explore and understand
rainbows, shadows and reflections, as well as discover innovative
uses of light in holograms, communications, medicine and much
 more.  The exhibit, which runs through December 1996,  is sponsored
by Pacific Gas &amp; Electric.
<P>
<U><B>Upcoming - Buzz Aldrin September 19</B></U>
<P>
Former astronaut and second man to walk on the moon, Buzz Aldrin,
will visit The Tech Museum of Innovation this fall.   On September
19 at 7 pm, Aldrin will be interviewed by radio host Moira Gunn
for her weekly NPR show, TechNation.  The public is invited. 
For more details, call 408-279-7157.
<P>
<U><B>Ongoing - WEB DEMONSTRATIONS </B></U>
<P>
Each Tuesday through Friday at lunch time, Tech staff members
will demonstrate the World Wide Web, providing basic &#147;how-to&#148;
instruction in exploring this user-friendly, graphical portion
of the Internet,  followed by hands-on opportunity for interested
visitors.  Try it yourself in a convenient and fun atmosphere.
 On Saturdays and Sundays, Web demonstrations will be presented
periodically throughout the day.  Free with paid museum admission.
<P>
<U><B>Workshops and Other Activities at The Tech</B></U>
<P>
The Tech Museum of Innovation hosts a variety of weekend hands-on
technology and computer workshops throughout the year.  Advance
registration is required, and fees include Museum admission. 
For a complete listing of  workshops or for more information,
call 408-279-7158.  


