<p><h3>Magic of Lasers, Light and Color Focus of New Exhibit at The
Tech</h3><b>SAN JOSE, CA, May 28, 1996</b> - The magic and mystery of
lasers, light and color will be revealed in a new exhibit opening June
15 at The Tech Museum of Innovation in San Jose.  Titled "Lasers,
Light & Color," the exhibit will explore holography and lasers in
every day use as well as in crime-solving, cancer treatment and
earthquake detection.  The exhibit will also examine the phenomenon of
light and color.<p>The exhibit will include floor demonstrations and
programs which explain laser basics, as well as everyday tools which
employ laser technology.  The exhibit explores topics from light
refraction to fluorescence to color blindness.  <p>The Tech Museum
developed displays on lasers and holograms which complement a
traveling exhibit from the Oregon Museum of Science and Industry
(OMSI) that features hands-on kiosks about light and color. Visitors
will be able to bend laser beams, view life-like holograms, split
white light into a rainbow of color and view their reflections from
odd angles. The exhibit runs through December 31, 1996.<p> PG&E is the
exhibit sponsor for "Lasers, Light & Color." In addition, Coherent,
Inc.,donated equipment used in the
exhibit.<p><center>###</center><p>http://www.thetech.org/news/pr-laser.html<hr>
