<p>
<h3>
</h3>
<p>
<U><B>SPECIAL HOLIDAY OPENING! AND THE TECH IS FREE!</B></U>  
<P> 
The Tech Museum of Innovation will be open on Labor Day, Monday, 
September 4, and, in conjunction with San Jose's annual arts festival, 
Tapestry In Talent, admission to The Tech is free for the Labor 
Day weekend, Saturday, September 2 through Monday September 4. 
Hours are 10 am to 5 pm. Each day, visitors can investigate bubbles, 
magnetic levitation and more at the exciting Science and Math 
Carnival activities provided Sandia National Laboratories; the 
Digital Playroom will be open in the Media Lab and The Tech will 
host an interactive outdoor exhibit as part of the Tapestry In 
Talent festival. 
<P> 
<U><B>HOME SCHOOL DAY AT THE TECH</B></U>  
<P> 
The Tech Museum of Innovation has set aside Tuesday, September 
19 as Home School Day at The Tech. Labs, usually used by school 
groups, will be offered for groups of home schoolers from all 
over the Bay area, and home schoolers and their parents will enjoy 
special lobby activities, floor demonstrations, tours, and the 
Digital Playroom. Home schoolers and their families will be admitted 
for the special group discount rate of $3 for students and $5 
for adults for this special day. Preregistration is required for 
labs and a separate fee applies; please call home school parent 
Jill Boone at (408) 379-6835 for information or registration. 
<P> 
<U><B>SPECIAL EXHIBIT !</B></U>  
<P> 
Visitors will &quot;Get Into Technology!&quot; this Fall at The 
Tech. <U><B>Virtual World: Multimedia and the Internet</B></U> 
allows visitors to &quot;test drive&quot; the Internet and new 
multimedia software. Among the many exhibits: new communications 
technology will take visitors to the underwater world of Monterey 
Bay via high speed, high capacity fiber optic link, and allow 
them to talk live with scientists and interpretive staff at the 
Monterey Bay Aquarium. At other stations, volunteer explainers 
will help visitors navigate various destinations on the World 
Wide Web, and at still others, visitors can experience amazing 
multimedia entertainment and education. In addition, the Multimedia 
Lab will be open most Tuesday and Thursday afternoons from 2:30 
to 5, and most weekend afternoons, to allow visitors to explore 
the latest multimedia software. 
<P> 
<U><B>INTERNET TUTORIAL WORKSHOPS!</B></U>  
<P> 
Each Sunday from 10 to 11:30, The Tech Museum of Innovation will 
offer a tutorial workshop on the Internet. Visitors will have 
extended time and hands-on opportunity to explore and develop 
skills in navigating the 'Net. No pre registration is required, 
and the workshop is free with paid museum admission. 
<P> 
<U><B>CALENDAR - Workshops and other Activities at The Tech</B></U> 
 
<P> 
The Tech Museum of Innovation hosts a variety of weekend hands-on 
technology and computer workshops throughout the year. Advance 
registration is suggested. For a complete listing of workshops 
or for more information, call (408) 279-7158. In addition, many 
special activities are free with paid Museum admission. 
