<P> 
The Tech Museum of Innovation is a hands-on museum featuring the 
emerging technologies of Silicon Valley and beyond. The Tech is 
located at 145 West San Carlos Street in downtown San Jose. Regular 
hours are 10:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m., Tuesday through Sunday. The 
Tech will be open on Labor Day, Monday, September 4. Admission 
is $6 for adults; $4 for youth, seniors and students. The Museum 
is on the Convention Center light rail stop. For general information 
call (408) 279-7150. 

