<hr>
<h3>Microserfs Author Douglas Coupland Selects The Tech Museum of Innovation for World's First Film Premiere in Chip Clean Room</h3>
<h3>Coupland to make book tour stop at The Tech on Wednesday, June 21</h3>
<b>SAN JOSE, CA - June 5, 1995 - </b> The Tech Museum of Innovation 
will play host to the world's first film premiere shown from a clean room on
Wednesday, June 21 at 6:30 pm.  The film, <i>Close Personal Friend</i>, is a
half-hour experimental documentary on author Douglas Coupland.  Produced and
directed by Toronto filmmaker Jennifer Cowan, <i>Close Personal Friend</i>
draws heavily from Coupland's new novel titled <i>Microserfs</i>, which
highlights Microsoft employees finding their way through Silicon Valley.
<p>
Participants will be invited to don clean room suits and view the film in The
Tech's simulated Clean Room, which is part of the museum's microelectronics
exhibit area.
<p>
The event at The Tech will be part of Coupland's ten-city tour promoting his
book.  Participants will also have an opportunity to meet Coupland, a
contributing writer for <i>Wired</i> magazine and the person responsible for
coining the expression "Generation X."
<p>
During his visit at The Tech, Coupland will give away signed works of art
suitable for framing and "<i>Microserfs</i> 1995 World Tour Official
Pre-moistened Towelettes," suitable for swabbing ... stuff ... from
screens of personal computers.
<p>
The Tech Museum of Innovation is an educational institution
established to engage people of all ages and backgrounds in exploring
today's technologies and to inspire young people to become the
technology innovators of tomorrow.  The four-year-old museum features
interactive exhibits on Space, Microelectronics, Materials, High-Tech
Bicycles, Biotechnology, Robotics and more.  The Tech is located at
145 West San Carlos Street in San Jose, California, and is open
Tuesday through Sunday from 10:00 AM to 5:00 PM.  For general
information, call (408) 279-7150.
<p>
Regular museum admission of $6 per adult and $4 youth and seniors is
being charged at the door.  The doors to the museum will be open at
6:00 p.m. for this event.
<p>
