<title>Six Named to Museum's Board of Directors</title>
<pre>
The Tech Museum of Innovation                     CONTACT:  Gloria Chun Hoo
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE                                       (408) 279-7157
June 13, 1994
</pre>
<h1>Six Named to Tech Museum of Innovation<br>
Board of Directors</h1>
 
SAN JOSE, CA (June 13, 1994) -- The Tech Museum of
Innovations last Thursday named six new members to its board of
directors.
<p>They are: <a href="/board-bio.html#harris">Jay T. Harris</a>, chairman and publisher, San Jose
Mercury News;  <a href="/board-bio.html#held">Gerald Held</a>, Ph.D., senior vice president, Oracle
Corporation; <a href="/board-bio.html#mccarthy">Gail McCarthy</a>, Ph.D., a consulting mechanical
engineer with Failure Analysis Associates and a member of the
Hearing Board for the Bay Area Air Quality District; 
<a href="/board-bio.html#cromwell">John P. Cromwell</a>, III, senior vice president, Bank of America; 
<a href="/board-bio.html#leeper">Harold
 Leeper</a>, a volunteer at The Tech and a retired principal scientist
with Alza Corporation; and <a href="/board-bio.html#tseng">Rose Tseng</a>, Ph.D., chancellor, West
Valley-Mission Community College District.
<p>They join a prestigious board that includes representation
from many Silicon Valley industries, educational institutions,
and businesses.  The board is currently engaged in a major
capital campaign to raise $20 million for exhibits and for
interior space in the museum's future building.
<p>The Tech Museum of Innovation is currently in prototype
space at 145 W. San Carlos Street in downtown San Jose, with a
mission to engage people of all backgrounds in exploring and
experiencing the technologies affecting their lives and to
encourage today's youth to become the innovators of technologies
of the future.                
<pre>
                                # # #
</pre>
