<title>The Tech Museum Goes Online on Apple's New eWorld</title>
<h1>Take an Online Tour of Silicon ValleyUs<br>
Tech Museum of Innovation in AppleUs New eWorld</h1>
<pre>
The Tech Museum of Innovation                       CONTACT:	Gloria Chun Hoo
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE                                 (408) 279-7157
</pre>
SAN JOSE, CA (June, 1994) -- The Tech Museum of Innovation, Silicon ValleyUs interactive high-tech museum, has now opened its doors to the world of online users through AppleUs newly-launched eWorld.
<p>
As an information provider in eWorld, The Tech will provide users with an online tour of its six exhibit areas; its InfoLounge and all temporary exhibits; feature a regular discussion board about topics such as ethics about emerging technologies; and host a series of guest speakers from Silicon Valley and beyond who will present informative, informal technology talks on eWorld.	
<p>
"Through eWorld, the Tech Museum of Innovation becomes a virtual museum able to reach large new museum audiences, " said Peter Giles, president of The Tech Museum of Innovation.  "With our online series of speakers, we will share with the world the energy of Silicon Valley, the innovative thinking that drives this special geographic area, and some of the raging debates about where technologyUs new frontiers are.  The Tech Museum of Innovation now has an electronic address on the Information Highway.  We hope the world will Tstop byU to visit us."
<p>
The technology talks with Silicon Valley experts will be hosted in the "auditorium," a place where online users gather interactively with other online users, ask real-time questions of the guest speakers, and even engage in dialogue with other users.  As many as 200 people will fill the auditorium for these talks, "sit" in auditorium seats, even get to know who their neighbors are, and like the real world...hold private conversations among themselves.  Meanwhile, on center stage, The Tech Museum of InnovationUs keynote speaker will be able to deliver remarks and respond to questions from the eWorld audience.
<p>
eWorld users will be able to electronically access a wide range of information about The Tech Museum of Innovation, its programs, schedule of workshops and weekend activities, school labs and teacher workshops, as well as find information on membership, volunteer opportunities, and updated plans for Future Tech.
<p>
Located in San Jose, which is frequently referred to as the "capital" of Silicon Valley, The Tech Museum of Innovation is a new generation museum with highly interactive, "hands-on" exhibits featuring technologies which are changing peopleUs lives.  Less basic science-oriented than technology-oriented, the museum offers visitors a chance to explore new and emerging technologies.  The museum opened three years ago in its "prototype" space.  There are six thematic exhibit areas feature: Microelectronics, Space, Robotics, New Materials, Bicycles, and Biotechnology.  Future plans for the museum include the construction of a new, significantly larger building with totally new visitor experiences planned and a broad range of exhibit topics to be featured: Silicon Society, Exploration on Earth and in Space, Life Tech, and the Communications Revolution.
<p>
The Tech Museum of Innovation is an educational resource which engages people of all ages and backgrounds in exploring and experiencing the technologies affecting their lives, and to inspire the young to become innovators in developing technologies of the future.
<p>
The Tech Museum of Innovation is a private, nonprofit, educational resource with funding from individual and corporate grants, membership support, admissions, gift store sales and the City of San Jose.  Located at 145 W. San Carlos Street in downtown San Jose, the museum hours are Tuesday through Sunday, 10 a.m. to 5 p.m.  For museum information, call (408) 279-7150.
<p>
###
