<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>AEF Programs</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY
BACKGROUND="backgrnd/vbar2.gif" BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#0000FF" LEFTMARGIN="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><A HREF="index.html"><IMG
SRC="images/torcher2.gif" ALT="Return to AEF Home Page" ALIGN="TOP" BORDER="0" VSPACE="0" HSPACE="12" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="59"></A>
<IMG
SRC="images/mission.gif" ALIGN="TOP" VSPACE="16" HSPACE="18" WIDTH="428" HEIGHT="42">
</P><P><IMG
SRC="backgrnd/spacer.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="1000" HSPACE="26" WIDTH="35" HEIGHT="4"></P><HR>
<P><H3 ALIGN="CENTER">AEF Programs - "A National Vision with a Local Focus"</H3>
<P>
<B>Educating America's Youth</B>
     <UL><LI> Visions of Exploration is a joint effort by USA Today newspaper and local Air
          Force Association Chapters to provide elementary teachers with a curriculum to
          enhance 4-6th graders understanding and appreciation for math and science.  It
          reaches approximately 75,000 students each year.  </UL> 
<P>
<B>Grants and Educational Assistance</B>
     <UL><LI>Chapter Matching Grants provide matching funds to AFA chapters for
          aerospace education activities to benefit their local communities
     <LI>Educator Grants support teachers with grants of up to $250 for an aerospace
          activity.
     <LI>AFJROTC Instructor Grants of $250 enable AFJROTC instructors to expand
          the aerospace and civics experiences for cadet. 
     <LI>Civil Air Patrol Aerospace Education Instructor Grants support CAP cadet
          squadrons with grants of up to $250 for new and innovative aerospace education
          programs.</UL>
<P>
<B>The Foundation's Information Program</B> assists teachers, students and others
     seeking information, educational materials, ideas and speakers for aerospace education
     programs.
<P>
<B>Awards and Recognition</B>
<UL><LI>Christa McAuliffe Memorial Award, AEF's National Teacher of the Year
          Award, is given annually to an educator who has gone "the extra mile" to
          increase student interest in math, science and technology.
     <LI>AEF Regional Teacher of the Year Awards recognize exceptional teachers in
          AFA's 14 regions.
     <LI>AFA Chapter Teacher of the Year Awards recognize outstanding efforts by local
teachers. 
     <LI>George D. Hardy Award is given to an AFA member for outstanding
          contributions in    aerospace education.
     <LI>Sam E. Keith, Jr. Award is awarded to an AFA Chapter for outstanding
          contributions  in aerospace education.
     <LI>AEF Fellowships are awarded for distinctive service to the nation, AFA, or           education.
     <LI>AFJROTC Contest challenges JROTC units world-wide to produce a video that  reinforces the mission of JROTC.
     <LI> AFJROTC Academic Excellence Award is awarded to cadets who maintain a
          GPA of at least 3.33 for two consecutive semesters.  The program is managed
          through AFJROTC headquarters.</UL>
<P>
<B>Scholarships</B>
<UL><LI>Eagle Grant Scholarship Program awards more than 500 educational grants of
          $250 to the Air Force's top enlisted graduates from the Community College of the
          Air Force  to pursue bachelor's degrees. 
     <LI>AEF Scholarships for Air Force Spouses provide $1,000 scholarships to
          spouses of Air Force active duty, Air National Guard and Air Force Reserve
          members who are pursuing undergraduate or graduate degrees. 
     <LI>Dr. Theodore von Karman Scholarships award $5,000 scholarships to top Air
          Force ROTC graduates each year for advanced degrees in math, engineering or a
          technical science.  </UL>
<P>
<B>Educating the Public</B>
<UL><LI>Publications:  AEF educates the public through various books and publications,
          Foundation Forums, Air Force National Defense Fellows Papers and the Defense
          & Airpower Series.
    <LI>Symposia: AEF sponsors symposia about important  issues facing the defense
          community.</UL>
<HR>
<P><I>For more information on AEF and its programs, please contact<A
HREF="mailto: AEFStaff@aef.org"> the Aerospace Education Foundation.</A></I></P>
<HR>
<A HREF="mission.html"><FONT SIZE="+2" COLOR="#FF0000">Return to the Mission, People and Programs Page</FONT></A>
</body>
</html>


