<TITLE>Supporting AEF Programs</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY
BACKGROUND="backgrnd/vbar2.gif" BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#0000FF" LEFTMARGIN="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<P ALIGN="LEFT"><A HREF="index.html"><IMG
SRC="images/torcher2.gif" ALT="Return to AEF Home Page" ALIGN="TOP" BORDER="0" VSPACE="0" HSPACE="12" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="59"></A>
<IMG SRC="images/mission.gif" ALIGN="TOP" VSPACE="16" HSPACE="18" WIDTH="428" HEIGHT="42">
</P>
<P><IMG SRC="backgrnd/spacer.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="1000" HSPACE="26" WIDTH="35" HEIGHT="4"></P><HR>
<P><H3 ALIGN="CENTER">How to financially support AEF programs 
</H3>
<P>
<I>AEF support for education, scholarship and recognition programs comes from the
generous support of businesses, individuals and AFA chapters.</I>
<P>
<B>Honorary Fellowships:</B> AFA members and chapters can designate a special Fellowship in honor of 
the significant contributions of individuals to the advancement or understanding of aerospace 
power through donations to support AEF programs.
<UL><LI>Barry Goldwater Fellow - $5,000 donation to AEF
    <LI>Ira C. Eaker or Jimmy Doolittle Fellow - $1,000 
    <LI>Full Fellow of the Foundation - $500
    <LI>Associate Fellow of the Foundation $250</UL>
<P>
<B>Corporate or individual donations</B> are used to support or endow specific education, scholarship 
or grant programs.  Some AFA members have established endowments through estate planning for the 
support of AEF programs and scholarships.  Please contact AEF by calling (703) 247-5839 if you 
would like to discuss a donation or corporate sponsorship. 
<P>
As <B>fundraising activities</B>, AEF sponsors two annual programs to solict donations for AEF 
education programs:
<UL><LI>Return Mail Address Label Program, involves customized return address labes with distinctive AFA or patriotic graphics, and
    <LI>Calendar with Airpower Art Series of great moments in aviation.</UL>
<P>
Supporting AEF in <B>Local Charity Campaigns</B>
<P>
The <B>Combined Federal Campaign (CFC)</B> season is coming up.  This year the Aerospace Education 
Foundation is involved again.  The AEF number is <B>1076</B> on the CFC form. The money received 
through CFC helps AEF support programs throughout the nation. The Foundation's "Nation Vision, 
Local Focus" means just that.  Seventy-five percent of the AEF budget goes to programs on the 
local level -- providing educational programs to 75,000 students and hundreds of grants to 
chapters, teachers, students and Jr. ROTC and Civil Air Patrol cadets.
<P>	
The Foundation is urging state and local chapters to encourage its members and people in the 
local community to remember the Foundation when they choose which organizations to give to in 
national and local charity campaigns like the <B>Combined Federal Campaign</B> and <B>United Way</B>. 
<P>
If you don't find AEF listed in the campaign guide book,  just write-in Aerospace Education 
Foundation and your contribution will be credited to the Foundation.   When your workplace 
participates in <B>CFC</B> or the <B>United Way</B> campaign, remember the Foundation -- <B>1076</B>.


<HR>
<P><I>For more information on how to financially support AEF's programs, or to request Address 
Labels or the current Calendar, please contact the Aerospace Education Foundation at 1501 Lee Highway, Arlington, Virginia, 22209-1198.  E-mail:<A HREF="mailto: AEFStaff@aef.org">AEFStaff@aef.org</A></I></P>
<HR>
