<TITLE>Chapter Matching Grants</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY
BACKGROUND="backgrnd/vbar2.gif" BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#0000FF" LEFTMARGIN="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<P><A HREF="index.html"><IMG
SRC="images/torcher2.gif" ALT="Return to AEF Home Page" ALIGN="TOP" BORDER="0" VSPACE="0" HSPACE="12" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="59"></A>
<IMG
SRC="images/afa_sup2.gif" ALIGN="TOP" BORDER="0" VSPACE="10" HSPACE="22" WIDTH="270" HEIGHT="54">
</P>
<P></P>
<P><IMG
SRC="backgrnd/spacer.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="1000" HSPACE="26" WIDTH="35" HEIGHT="4"></P><HR>
<H2 ALIGN=center>Chapter Matching Grants for Aerospace Education Programs</H2>
     
The AFA Chapter Matching Grant program was established to promote aerospace education
activities at chapters level where funds are limited.  It gives chapters an opportunity to enhance
their community's ideas about how aerospace plays a prominent role in today and tomorrow's
society.  For each dollar a chapter contributes to an aerospace education program, the chapter
may request up to $1,000 in matching funds.
<P>
<B>Typically chapters request Matching Grants for:</B>
   <UL><LI>Science Fairs.
   <LI>Field Trips.
   <LI>Aerospace activities with schools such as JROTC & ROTC units.
   <LI>Career Days.</UL>
<P>
<B>Matching Grants May Not Be Used For:</B>
   <UL><LI>Scholarships.
   <LI>Non-math/science/technology/aerospace activities.
   <LI>To pay for the chapter's share of Visions of Exploration.</UL> 
<P>
Applications for matching grants are evaluated by AEF based on the importance and impact of
the chapter's activity.  Within four to six weeks AEF will let your chapter contact person know if
the grant was approved or not.  Chapters may apply for more than one grant per calendar year as
long as the total amount requested is less than $1,000.
<P>
When a chapter receives a grant, the check will sent to the chapter contact.
AEF would like to hear how the activity turned out.  Please send photos (action shots) and a short
description on how the activity went.
<P>
<B>Application</B>
<OL><LI>Chapter Name
    <LI>Chapter contact (any chapter member) with phone and address
    <LI>Description of activity, location, date and number of people involved/benefiting
    <LI>Budget for the activity/project
    <LI>Amount requested (up to $1,000) and amount being contributed by the chapter
    <LI>Signatures of chapter president and treasurer</OL>
          
<HR>
Send e-mail to <A HREF="mailto: AEFStaff@aef.org">AEFStaff@aef.org</A>
<HR>

