</P>
<P><IMG
SRC="backgrnd/spacer.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="1000" HSPACE="26" WIDTH="35" HEIGHT="4"></P>
<HR><H2 ALIGN=center>Direct Grants to Teachers, JROTC units and Civil Air Patrol
Squadrons</H2>
<P>
AEF offers <B>Teacher</B>, <B>JROTC</B> and <B>CAP Grants</B> to promote aerospace education for teachers
where funds are not otherwise available. Teacher Grants provide up to $250 per academic year in
support to elementary and secondary classrooms for aerospace education programs,
opportunities, activities and interest when no support is available currently.  JROTC and CAP
units may also apply for up to $250 during the academic year for aerospace education programs. 
Local AFA chapters can furnish information about the program to local schools, and AFJROTC
and CAP units.  Applications are available from the Aerospace Education Foundation, 1501 Lee
Highway, Arlington, VA 22209-1198.  
 <P>    
<B>Use of Grants</B>
<BLOCKQUOTE>Funds can be used for anything related to aerospace, from
purchasing textbooks or videotapes, to going on a field trip to an
aerospace museum, Air Force base or other aerospace facility. </BLOCKQUOTE> 

<B>Application</B>
<UL><LI>Sponsoring teacher's name, school address and subject and grade.
<LI>Purpose of the grant and amount requested
<LI>Previous aerospace related activities in the classroom.
<LI>Verification/certification by Principal/Instructor</UL>
<HR>
Send e-mail to <A HREF="mailto: AEFStaff@aef.org">AEFStaff@aef.org</A>
