<HEAD>
<TITLE>Sam E. Keith, Jr., AEF Award of Excellence</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY
BACKGROUND="backgrnd/vbar2.gif" BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#0000FF" LEFTMARGIN="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<P><A HREF="index.html"><IMG
SRC="images/torcher2.gif" ALT="Return to AEF Home Page" ALIGN="TOP" BORDER="0" VSPACE="0" HSPACE="12" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="59"></A><IMG
SRC="images/afa_sup2.gif" ALIGN="TOP" BORDER="0" VSPACE="10" HSPACE="22" WIDTH="270" HEIGHT="54">
</P>
<P><IMG
SRC="backgrnd/spacer.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="1000" HSPACE="26" WIDTH="35" HEIGHT="4"></P><HR>
<H3 ALIGN="CENTER">Sam E. Keith, Jr., Aerospace Education Foundation Award of Excellence</H3>

The Sam E. Keith, Jr. Aerospace Education Award of Excellence is given to an
AFA Chapter, in recognition of continuing efforts to further the scientific and
technical education of youth through the use of aerospace education and historical
materials. 
<P>
The award is named in honor of the late Sam E. Keith, Jr., former AFA President
and Chairman of the Board, who had a deep interest in the Foundation and the state
of America's technical education. It is given in recognition of efforts to further the
scientific and technical education of students through the use of aerospace
education and historical aviation materials and programs sponsored in conjunction
with an Air Force Association chapter.  
<P>
A representative from the winning chapter will be honored at the Aerospace
Education Foundation luncheon on Monday, September 15, 1997. (The
representative will be flown to Washington, DC on Saturday, September 13 and can
anticipate departing sometime after 3 p.m. on Monday, September 15. AEF will
cover the costs for one coach class, round-trip airline ticket and two nights lodging
at the Sheraton Washington Hotel.) 
<P>
<B>Selection Criteria</B>
<P>
<OL><LI>AFA chapters must be in good standing. 
    <LI>Nomination must be endorsed by AFA State President and AFA National Vice
       President (letters of support/endorsement should be included with the nomination/
       application).     
    <LI>Extensive documentation is required. A viable nomination will include the
        following: a complete synopsis of educational programs which should outline
        chapter goals, community involvement, number of students affected, program
        impact and photographic documentation; letters of recommendation from students,
        educators, and community leaders; and any publicity or press coverage.     
    <LI>Complete the application form and submit it with all the information in one
       loose-leaf notebook. The notebook should not exceed one inch thick. Videotapes
        will not be accepted.  </OL>
<P>
The judging of all entries will be conducted at AFA National Headquarters under
the management of the AEF staff. 
<P>
<B>Deadline for 1997 Award</B>
     Nominations for the 1997 Keith Award must be postmarked by June 9, 1997.
<P>
<B>Prior AFA Winners</B>
     <UL><LI>1991 Jule Zumwalt - Sacramento, Calif.
<LI>     1992 Kenneth O. Wofford - Golden Valley, Minn.
<LI>     1993 John R. "Bob" White - Fatetteville, N.C.
<LI>     1994 Alamo Chapter of San Antonio, Texas
<LI>     1995 Dr. Phillip Brieske - Honolulu, Hawaii</UL>
<HR>
