<HEAD>
<TITLE>1997 George D. Hardy Memorial Award</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY
BACKGROUND="backgrnd/vbar2.gif" BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#0000FF" LEFTMARGIN="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<P><A HREF="index.html"><IMG
SRC="images/torcher2.gif" ALT="Return to AEF Home Page" ALIGN="TOP" BORDER="0" VSPACE="0" HSPACE="12" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="59"></A><IMG
SRC="images/afa_sup2.gif" ALIGN="TOP" BORDER="0" VSPACE="10" HSPACE="22" WIDTH="270" HEIGHT="54">
</P>
<P><IMG
SRC="backgrnd/spacer.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="1000" HSPACE="26" WIDTH="35" HEIGHT="4"></P><HR>
<H3 ALIGN="CENTER">1997 George D. Hardy Memorial Award</H3>


The George D. Hardy Aerospace Education Award of Excellence is given to an individual in
recognition of continuing efforts to further the scientific and technical education of youth through
the use of aerospace education and historical materials. 
<P>
The award is named in honor of the late George D. Hardy, former AFA leader who served either
as a member or chairman of almost every AFA national committee. He was a National Director
for 45 years.  He was a member, from the beginning, of the Aerospace Education Foundation's
Board of Trustees, and served as the Foundation's Treasurer, Secretary, President and on two
different occasions, as its Chairman. 
<P>
The winner will be honored at the Aerospace Education Foundation luncheon on Monday,
September 15, 1997. (The winning applicant will be flown to Washington, DC on Saturday,
September 13 and can anticipate departing sometime after 3 p.m. on Monday, September 15.
AEF will cover the costs for one coach class, round-trip airline ticket and two nights lodging at
the Sheraton Washington Hotel.) 
<P>
<B>Selection Criteria</B>

<OL><LI>Individual must be an AFA member in good standing and affiliated and active
with his/her particular chapter. 
    <LI>Aerospace education program must be affiliated with and managed by the local AFA chapter.     
    <LI>Nomination must be endorsed by AFA State President and AFA National Vice
        President (letters of support/endorsement should be included with the nomination/application).     
    <LI>Extensive documentation of your project is required. A viable nomination will
        include the following: a complete synopsis of the program which should outline its
        goals, community involvement, number of students affected, program impact and
        photographic documentation; letters of recommendation from students, educators,
        and community leaders; and any publicity or press coverage.     
    <LI>Complete the application form and submit it with all the information in one
        loose-leaf notebook. The notebook should not exceed one inch thick. Videotapes
        will not be accepted.  
    <LI>Members nominated can not have received the award previously. 
    </OL>
<P>
The judging of all entries will be conducted at AFA National Headquarters under
the management of the AEF staff. 
<P>
<B>Deadline for 1997 Award
     Nominations for the 1997 Hardy Award must be postmarked by June 9,
1997.</B>
<P>

<HR>
