<HEAD>
<TITLE>How Are AEF Programs Funded?</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY
BACKGROUND="backgrnd/vbar2.gif" BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#0000FF" LEFTMARGIN="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<P><A HREF="index.html"><IMG
SRC="images/torcher2.gif" ALT="Return to AEF Home Page" ALIGN="TOP" BORDER="0" VSPACE="0" HSPACE="12" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="59"></A><IMG
SRC="images/afa_sup2.gif" ALIGN="TOP" BORDER="0" VSPACE="10" HSPACE="22" WIDTH="270" HEIGHT="54">
</P>
<P><IMG
SRC="backgrnd/spacer.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="1000" HSPACE="26" WIDTH="35" HEIGHT="4"></P><HR>
<H2 ALIGN="CENTER">How Are AEF Programs Funded?</H2>
<P>              

AEF support for education, scholarship and recognition programs comes from the generous
support of businesses, individuals and AFA chapters.  The Foundation's "Nation Vision, Local
Focus" means just that.  Seventy-five percent of the AEF budget goes to programs on the local
level -- providing educational programs to 75,000 students and hundreds of grants to chapters,
teachers, students and Jr. ROTC and Civil Air Patrol cadets.
<P>
    <UL><LI> <B>AEF Honorary Fellowship Programs</B>
     The Fellowship Program allows individuals, chapters and corporations to support the
     Aerospace Education Foundation by honoring individuals and groups who have made
     significant contributions to the advancement or understanding of aerospace education. 
     Through donations, they can designate a jimmy Doolittle Fellow, an Ira C. Eaker Fellow,
     and AEF Fellow or an Associate AEF Fellow:  
       <UL><LI>Barry Goldwater Fellow - $5,000 donation to AEF
          <LI>Ira C. Eaker or Jimmy Doolittle Fellow - $1,000 donation
       <LI>Full Fellow of the Foundation - $500 donation
       <LI>Associate Fellow of the Foundation $250 donation</UL></UL>
<P>
     <UL><LI><B>Corporate and individual donations</B> are used to support or endow specific education,
     scholarship or grant programs.  Some AFA members have established endowments
     through estate planning for the support of AEF programs and scholarships.  Please
     contact AEF by calling (703) 247-5839 if you would like to discuss a donation or
     corporate sponsorship. </UL>
<P>
     <UL><LI><B>Fundraising activities:</B> AEF sponsors two annual fundraising programs to support AEF
     education programs: 
      <UL><LI> <B>Return Mail Address Label Program</B> involves customized return address labels
       with distinctive AFA or patriotic graphics.  The labels are so popular with many AFA
       members that they order additional copies for their friends. 
        <LI>  <B>AFA Airpower Art Series Calendar</B> is distributed to AFA members and friends of
          AEF.  Each year a new series of paintings depicting great moments in the history of
          aviation adorns the walls of members.</UL></UL>
<P>
     If you would like to make a donation to AEF and receive personalized <B>Address Labels</B> or
     an <B>AFA Calendar</B>, please send an e-mail request to <A HREF="mailto: AEFStaff@aef.org">AEFStaff@aef.org</A> with your name
     and address.
<P>
<P>
<CENTER><H3>Supporting AEF in Local Charity Campaigns</H3></CENTER>
<P>
The <B>Combined Federal Campaign (CFC)</B> season is coming up.  This year the Aerospace
Education Foundation is involved again.  The AEF number is 1076 on the CFC form. The money
received through CFC helps AEF support programs throughout the nation.
  <P>
Please remember the Foundation when choosing which organizations to give to in national and
local charity campaigns like the <B>Combined Federal Campaign</B> and <B>United Way</B>. 
<P>
If you don't find AEF listed in the campaign guide book,  just write-in Aerospace Education
Foundation and your contribution will be credited to the Foundation.   When your workplace
participates in <B>CFC</B> or the <B>United Way campaign</B>, remember the Foundation -- <B>1076</B>.
<P>

For more information on how to financially support AEF's programs, or to request Address
Labels or the current Calendar, please contact the Aerospace Education Foundation at 1501 Lee
Highway, Arlington, Virginia, 22209-1198.  E-mail: <A HREF="mailto: AEFStaff@aef.org">AEFStaff@aef.org</A>.
<HR>
