<TITLE>IDEA Forum</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY
BACKGROUND="backgrnd/vbar2.gif" BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#0000FF" LEFTMARGIN="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<P><A HREF="index.html"><IMG
SRC="images/torcher2.gif" ALT="Return to AEF Home Page" ALIGN="TOP" BORDER="0" VSPACE="0" HSPACE="12" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="59"></A><IMG
SRC="images/afa_sup2.gif" ALIGN="TOP" BORDER="0" VSPACE="10" HSPACE="22" WIDTH="270" HEIGHT="54">
</P>
<P><IMG
SRC="backgrnd/spacer.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="1000" HSPACE="26" WIDTH="35" HEIGHT="4"></P><HR>
<H2 ALIGN="CENTER">IDEA Forum</H2>
<P>
                           
                                
<B>AFA Chapter Matching Grant Stories:</B>
<P>
    <UL><LI> The Golden Triangle Air Force Association chapter in Mississippi received $350 from AEF
     and added its matching funds to pay for food, rooms, and registration for three public school
     teachers to attend the Mississippi Science Teachers association conference to present a
     program entitled, "Aerodynamics is a Dynamite Way to Teach Problem Solving."  The three
     teachers showed the conference participants how a series of activities involving flight could
     give children new skills in logical thinking.  The session ended with a discussion of AEF
     programs and the Visions of Exploration program. 
<P>
     <LI>The Lance P. Sijan Chapter in Colorado sponsored four partial fellowships for educators to
     attend the "Getting Comfortable Teaching with Space Course" held at the Air Force
     Academy.  The course taught educators how to incorporate space and aviation concepts into
     all areas of their curriculum as a way to stimulate student achievement.
<P>
    <LI>The Delaware State AFA requested funding to cover half the cost of a trailer to support a
     statewide aviation program.  A Boeing K-3 flight Simulator and 10 Hartel Preflight
     Classroom Trainer was transported to different schools throughout the state.  During the
     1995-96 academic year, over 3,700 young people in grades K-3 had a chance to fly in the
     simulator.</UL>
<P>
<B>Special Programs: </B> 
<P>
     <UL><LI>Following the tragic crash of an Alaskan-based AWACS E-3 in 1995, the Anchorage AFA
     established a scholarship fund for the children of the crewmembers.  With AEF support, the
     fund will provide scholarships for post high school academic or training programs to each of
     the Yukla 27 crew's children.  The actual size of each scholarships will depend on the final
     size of the scholarship fund. </UL>
<P>
<B><I>AEF welcomes submissions from AFA chapters on local programs that have been successful in
promoting aerospace education.  Please send an e-mail note to AEF describing your local chapter
program so we can include it on the IDEA FORUM.  </I></B>
<P>
Send e-mail to <A HREF="mailto: AEFStaff@aef.org">AEFStaff@aef.org</A>.

