</P>
<P><IMG
SRC="backgrnd/spacer.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="1000" HSPACE="26" WIDTH="35" HEIGHT="4"></P><HR>
<H2 ALIGN=center>Educator Grants for Aerospace Related School Projects</H2>
<P>AEF offers Educator Grants to promote aerospace education for teachers where funds are not
otherwise available. Educator Grants provide up to $250 per calendar year in support to
elementary and secondary classrooms for aerospace education programs, opportunities, activities
and interest when no support is available currently.  Applications are available from the
Aerospace Education Foundation, 1501 Lee Highway, Arlington, VA 22209-1198.  
<P>     
<B> Use of Grants</B>
   <UL><LI>  Funds can be used for anything related to aerospace, from purchasing textbooks or
     videotapes, to going on a field trip to an aerospace museum, Air Force base or other
     aerospace facility.  
</UL>
<P>
<B>Application</B>
<UL><LI>Sponsoring teacher's name, school address and subject and grade.
<LI>Purpose of the grant and amount requested
<LI>Previous aerospace related activities in the classroom.
<LI>Verification/certification by Principal
</UL>
<P>
<HR>
Send e-mail to <A HREF="mailto: AEFStaff@aef.org">AEFStaff@aef.org</A>
<HR>
