<TITLE>AEF Resources for Educators &amp; Students</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY
BACKGROUND="backgrnd/vbar2.gif" BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#0000FF" LEFTMARGIN="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<P><A HREF="index.html"><IMG
SRC="images/torcher2.gif" ALT="Return to AEF Home Page" ALIGN="TOP" BORDER="0" VSPACE="0" HSPACE="12" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="59"></A>
<IMG
SRC="images/resource.gif" ALIGN="TOP" VSPACE="16" HSPACE="6" WIDTH="430" HEIGHT="30">
</P>
<P><IMG
SRC="backgrnd/spacer.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="1000" HSPACE="26" WIDTH="35" HEIGHT="4"></P>
<HR><H3 ALIGN=center>AEF Information Program</H3>

A little known, but extremely busy, Foundation activity is providing information
about everything from careers in aerospace to educational program materials
published by the National Aeronautics and Space Administration, the Federal
Aviation Administration and others. Thousands of requests for information are
received from teachers, students and others every year. Each request is answered
and thousands of publications are distributed. This Foundation service also provides
materials for distribution at local aviation fairs, career fairs and school vocational
activities. 
<P>
<UL><LI>AEF and AFA Resources/Pamphlets

<LI>NASA Materials<A HREF="http://www.okstate.edu/aesp/AESP.html">NASA Aerospace Education Services Program</a>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.faa.gov/">FAA Materials</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.nas.edu/">National Academy of Science</a>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.nsta.org/">National Science Teachers Association</a>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.nsf.gov/">National Science Foundation</a>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.cstea.howard.edu/">Center for the Study of Terrestrial & Extraterrestrial Atmosphere</a> 
<LI>E-mail requests: <B><A HREF="mailto: AEFStaff@aef.org">AEFStaff@aef.org</A></B></ADDRESS></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
</UL><HR>
