<HEAD>
<TITLE>Eagle Grant Scholarship</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY
BACKGROUND="backgrnd/vbar2.gif" BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#0000FF" LEFTMARGIN="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<P><A HREF="index.html"><IMG
SRC="images/torcher2.gif" ALT="Return to AEF Home Page" ALIGN="TOP" BORDER="0" VSPACE="0" HSPACE="12" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="59"></A>
<IMG
SRC="images/scholar.gif" ALIGN="TOP" VSPACE="16" HSPACE="18" WIDTH="373" HEIGHT="31">
<P><IMG
SRC="backgrnd/spacer.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="1000" HSPACE="26" WIDTH="35" HEIGHT="4"></P>
<P>
<H2 ALIGN="CENTER">AEF Scholarships and Grants</H2><HR>

<H3>AEF Eagle Grant Scholarship Program </H3></B>
<p>

AEF Awards 500 one-time educational grants of $250 to the Air Force's top enlisted
     graduates from the Community College of the Air Force to pursue bachelor's degrees. 
     Open to all active duty bases and reserve component bases which produce the highest ratio of CCAF graduates
     , these grants are endowed by
     the Aerospace Education Foundation through corporate contributions and donations from
     Air Force Association members and chapters.  
<P>
Awards are selected based upon:
<UL><LI>Academic achievement, 
    <LI>Leadership, and 
    <LI>Extra-curricular activities.</UL>
<P>
Local AFA Chapter representative should coordinate with their local Base Education offices
 for arrangement and disbursal of checks, certificates
 and free one-year memberships in AFA for the graduates. 
<P>    
For further information check with the base Education office for an application and the
     deadline for the Fall 1997 program or contact the Aerospace Education Foundation, 1501
     Lee Highway, Arlington, Virginia 22209-1198.  Phone (703) 247-5839. 
     <B><A HREF="mailto: AEFStaff@aef.org">AEFStaff@aef.org</A></B>
<P>
<B>SELECTION CRITERIA</B>
<P>
<UL><LI>Local criteria are determined at the base level by a committee of the Base Director of
     Personnel, Base Education Officer, Senior Enlisted Advisor and a local Air Force
     Association (AFA) representative.       
<LI>The Selection Committee considers job performance, scholastic achievement, educational
     goals and leadership qualities. 
<LI>Need is not a principal criterion, and total achievements will be carefully considered by
     the selection committee. 
<P>    
<B>ELIGIBILITY REQUIREMENTS</B>
<P>
<UL><LI>Military rank: E-4, E-5, E-6 or E-7 
    <LI>CCAF Air Force graduate
    <LI>Graduated within the last two years
    <LI>May only receive the grant one time
    <LI>Be enrolled or will be enrolled in an accredited program leading to a baccalaureate
     degree.  
    <LI>Must submit application, narrative and documentation (see application) to a base
     Education Office. </UL>
<P>
       Send e-mail <B><A HREF="mailto: AEFStaff@aef.org">AEFStaff@aef.org</A></B> requesting application or further info.

<P>
<HR>
