<H2 ALIGN="CENTER">AEF Scholarships and Grants</H2><HR>

<H3>AFROTC Angel Flight and Silver Wing Society Scholarships</H3>

Aerospace Education Foundation's Angel Flight/Silver Wings Society Scholarship program provides 
$1,000 grants to rising juniors and seniors who are active members of Angel Flight/Silver Wings 
Society. 
<P>
This award, started in 1993, was established to recognize members of AnF/SWS for their academic 
excellence, their continued support of their communities and their dedication to the goals and 
initiatives of ROTC and the United States Air Force.  Angel Flight Scholarships are to be used 
for the purpose of tuition assistance.  Funding for the Angel Flight/Silver Wings Society 
Scholarships is provided by AFA Members and Chapters worldwide. 
<P>
<B>ELIGIBILITY REQUIREMENTS</B>
<UL><LI>Active member of Angel Flight/Silver Wings Society for a minimum of one year. 
    <LI>Junior or Senior student for academic year 1997-98 
    <LI>Mimimum Grade Point Average (GPA) of 3.0. 
    <LI>Ability to demonstrate active involvement in campus and community service projects.       
    <LI>Projects positive image of AnF/SWS, AFROTC, USAF. 
    <LI>Recommended by an AF/SWS advisor. </UL>
<P>
<B>NOMINATIONS MUST BE POSTMARKED BY: February 10, 1997</B>

<P><B>Send e-mail to: <A HREF="mailto: AEFStaff@aef.org">AEFStaff@aef.org</A></B>
<HR>
<B>Angel Flight/Silver Wings Scholarship Winners</B>
<P>
The ten winners each receive a $1,000 scholarship based upon their academic excellence, their continued support of their communities and their dedication to the goals and initiatives of ROTC and the U.S. Air Force.
<P>
LaShawna Beasley<BR>
Texas Tech University -- Speech Pathology
<P>
Karen Bottom<BR>
Louisiana Tech University -- Mechanical Engineering
<P>
Dayna Colflesh<BR>
Texas Christian University -- Habilitation of the Deaf
<P>
Allison Dworschak<BR>
Clemson University -- Psychology
<P>
Claire Henley<BR>
University of Southern Mississippi -- Elementary Education
<P>
Kristen Lloyd<BR>
Texas A&M University -- Chemistry
<P>
Heather  Miller<BR>
University of Texas at Austin -- Elementary Education
<P>
Jeanne  Partin<BR>
University of North Carolina -- Charlotte -- Nursing
<P>
Victoria Vaughn<BR>
University of Washington -- Chemical Engineering
<P>
Sharon  Waller<BR>
Auburn University -- Family and Child Development
