<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Officers and Trustees</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY
BACKGROUND="backgrnd/vbar2.gif" BGCOLOR="#C0C0C0" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#0000FF" LEFTMARGIN="0" TOPMARGIN="0">
<H2><A HREF="index.html"><IMG
SRC="images/torcher2.gif" ALT="Return to AEF Home Page" ALIGN="TOP" BORDER="0" VSPACE="0" HSPACE="12" WIDTH="46" HEIGHT="59"></A>
<IMG
SRC="images/officers.gif" ALIGN="TOP" VSPACE="16" HSPACE="22" WIDTH="298" HEIGHT="38"></H2>
<P><IMG
SRC="backgrnd/spacer.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" VSPACE="1000" HSPACE="26" WIDTH="35" HEIGHT="4"></P><HR>
                      <CENTER>Phillip E. Lacombe<br>
                       Managing Director<br>
                 Aerospace Education Foundation<br></CENTER>

<P>
In January 1994, Mr. Lacombe began serving as the Managing Director of the Aerospace
Education Foundation, a non-profit educational affiliate of the Air Force Association.  As the
Foundation's chief operating officer, he is responsible to the President and Board of Trustees for
all aspects of leadership, management, program development, fundraising and operations of the
foundation.
<P>
He also serves as a consultant to numerous commissions and panels on national security issues. 
Most recently, he served with the Commission on Roles and Missions of the Armed Forces as a
member of the Staff Executive Director's management team.  He was responsible for the
integration and writing of the final report, including all implementation documents, interim
reports and communications. 
<P>
Mr. Lacombe served with the United States Air Force and retired as a Colonel after more than 20
years active duty service on January 1, 1994.   His last duty was as Directory of Public Affairs at
U.S. and Air Force Space Commands and North American Aerospace Defense Command in
Colorado Springs.  
<P>
He has an M.A. in Journalism from the University of North Carolina and a B.A. in English from
the University of Massachusetts.
<P><HR>
